writer_story: Arianna and her dog were sailing on a boat across the Baltic Sea. The journey was long but so adventures. She was trying to cross the sea from Sweden to Poland so she could meet her one true love. They have been writing letters to each other for 18 months and decided it was time to meet. Arianna had her trip planned before she spoke to Leo for the first time. Since he lived in Poland it felt like faith. When she arrived to port she could see him waiting on shore, waving in excitement. She ran to him and it felt like she knew him forever.

On a moonlit night, beneath a starry sky, Alex, set sail across the open seas. Armed with dreams of treasure and foreign lands, he dared to uncover the mysteries that lay beyond the horizon. The melody of crashing waves and the distant call of seagulls guided his journey. As Alex's ship glided through turquoise waters, a huge storm arose, challenging his resolve. But Alex, fueled with resilience, steered through the chaos of the churning waters with a steady hand. Many moons after, a breathtaking encounter awaited him, as he stumbled upon a hidden mermaid sanctuary, their infectious songs captivating Alex's heart. Encouraged by his newfound allies, Alex navigated the treacherous waters and perilous currents, finally discovering an ancient treasure lost to time. With the treasure secured, Alex returned home, forever transformed by the enchantment of the open seas.

Becky knew she wasn't supposed to take her father's boat out of the harbour onto the open sea by herself, but it was a lovely day and the sea was still and calm, she'd watched her father operate the boat more times than she could remember so she felt confident as she started the motor and headed out.      Becky turned her face upwards towards the warm sun and closed her eyes, blissfully enjoying the heat and the sound of the water lapping at the sides of the boat.   She felt a shadow pass overhead and opened her eyes, delighted to see the seagull flying over her head and the three others who had joined their brother, she felt giddy as they circled above her with their shrieking cries. Suddenly one of the gulls swooped lower and she felt a stabbing pain in her head as it's beak connected with it, another beak flew into her face and she screamed as she felt her flesh tear. Beak after razor-sharp beak pecked at her head and slashed her arms as she tried to protect herself. Blood was running down her face into her eyes and she could no longer see.   She curled into a ball at the bottom of the boat and waited for the onslaught to stop, and she waited and she waited and she waited. By mid-afternoon the next day an empty boat was seen gently drifting into the harbour.

Rachel and Emily crouched to look at the tiny, dark spider.  'Careful Rach,' Emily warned, resting her hand on her sister's. 'That might be venomous.'  'But Mrs Webb told us to find the most interesting thing we could.'  Emily stood up, stretching her back as she looked up at the high canopy of the trees and then around at the shadowy forest floor. They'd wandered quite a way from the college group and she couldn't hear anyone else, or anything else for that matter.  'Do you remember the way back Rach?'  'We just need to follow the string you teased me for bringing,' Rachel said with a laugh.

A group of young, daring explorers have embarked upon a dangerous expedition in order to unearth ancient relics hidden for centuries in the heart of the jungle. Much to their horror, they quickly realise that they are not alone, as an unknown and ferocious creature is lurking in the shadows - ready to maim and kill. Amidst the tangled vines and the endless thick, towering trees - the group find themselves in mortal danger while, but they are determined to unearth the relics to solve the mysteries behind a lost civilization.  Jacob, the leader of the group, has been digging for what seems an age when he notices something glistening in the sunlight. Excited, he calls on his right hand man, Ian, to help with the delicate excavation project. Just as he begins to bring the relic to the surface, the creature jumps on his back - knocking him to the ground. Jacob screams in agony as the creature makes a fatal bite into his neck; he knows he is not going to make it. With his last dying breath he manages to alert the others in the group to the mortal danger they face, and pleads with them to run and leave the place as fast as he can, leaving him to die in the jungle.

John, an explorer and adventurer, had a lifelong ambition to enter the mysterious jungle where nobody before him had survived, and at long last he embarked on his mission to seek the legendary lost city of Perditum.  During the first few days of his adventure, John acclimatised himself with the jungle, seeking out safe vegetation to eat, building makeshift shelters along the way and keeping out of the way of dangerous animals.  After two weeks of pushing deeper into the jungle, he stumbled upon a settlement of mudhuts, where he saw  groups of native women, some cooking food over fires, some sitting by the river washing clothes, as they watched their children playing happily in the distance.  Suddenly one of the women started screaming hysterically and it soon became clear that her child was missing; John ran across to the group, who, startled at first at seeing a stranger in their midst, desperately pointed to an area of dense undergrowth behind the huts.  It became clear that the child had been seen running towards the undergrowth, but when John ventured in that direction, the women tried to stop him, looks of sheer terror on their faces, and emitting bloodcurdling screams as he ignored their warnings and ran towards the deep undergrowth.  As he ventured further, the jungle became thicker, and after two hours of struggling through the dense growth, sustaining cuts and bruises and being bitten by insects, he stumbled, falling and hitting his head on a stump, whereupon he passed out.  As he regained consciousness, he remembered a vivid dream that he must have experienced whilst unconscious, where he was floundering in a swamp, desperately trying to get out, before succumbing to the abyss; when suddenly a small boy appeared from nowhere and miraculously pulled him to safety, after which, John knew he had to carry on and find the missing boy.  He got to his feet and staggered on, gradually becoming stronger, when suddenly a clearing appeared in the jungle, and John could hardly believe what he was witnessing: the long lost city he had set out to discover, and here was the missing boy, looking bewildered and lost; John hauled him up onto his shoulders and began the long journey back to the safety of the boy's home village.

We set sail on the morning of June the 26th 1892.  Or destination was kept secret from us, only the captain and his mates knew.  Guns and weapons had been put on board so we had some trepidation.  The sea was rough and the ship was taking a battering, it would be a long voyage ahead.  A few days into the voyage we came across another ship in our path, the captain ordered us to take arms.  We were instructed to open fire on the vessel despite no aggression being shown towards us.  The other ship was still afloat but most of the crew had been killed.  We boarded the depleted ship and found treasure aboard which we looted for our own ends.

Kye peered over the edge of the boat and shuddered. The thick mass of water undulated below him, dark and impenetrable. They still had 600 miles before reaching Hamlet Cove, and the way was looking grim. Up ahead was a wall of grey cloud, and following them from the South, the same. The ship was quiet that day. They all knew what challenges lay ahead, and an unnerving presence hung in the air. Kye turned to the captain. He had never seen him look so pale.

This is my story.  There were 8 of us on a journey to another planet to look for life.  As we touched down on Mars we were greeted by a group of Ant-like looking creatures.  We were led to their king who was in a very large Ant-like palace.  The Ant King thanked us for coming and told us that we must take better care of our planet earth otherwise we would destroy its resources within 100 years.      We were shown around the palace and saw how these creatures used the resources available to them to be sustainable and have economic growth within their communities.  We lived with the Ant people for 3 months learning and being educated by them about everything.  I had a wonderful time on Mars we are not alone in the universe.  I learnt a word when living on Mars: TICKI it means LOVE

Deep within the heart of a lush, unexplored jungle, a young explorer named Amelia set out on a thrillng adventure. Equipped with her trusty map and a spirit of curiosity. she trekked through the dense foliage, guided only by the sounds of exotic birds and rustling leaves. The humid air hung heavy around her as she discovered ancient ruins, entangled with vines and mystery. As dusk settled, Amelia's flashlight illuminated the glowing eyes of a magnificent black panther, causing her heart to race with both fear and awe. With quick thinking, she cautiously befriended the majestic creature, who became her loyal companion in navigating treacherous terrain and warding off hidden dangers. Together, they stumbled upon a hidden treasure trove, brimming with sparkling jewels and ancient artifacts, remnants of a forgotten civilization. Overwhelmed by the awe-inspiring discovery, Amelia couldn't help but marvel at the untamed beauty of the jungle and the boundless adventures it held within its leafy embrace.

On the distant planet of Jupitero, a young explorer named Max embarked on a thrilling adventure to the uncharted planet. Equipped with his trusty telescope and robot dog - named xaM - he scanned and explored, taking note of what he found. Scanning the barren terrain, he discovered a hidden cave - hidden, yet radiating with a pulsating hum and glow. Stepping inside, he encountered a mystical beast named Star, who enlightened Max with the lore and history of the planet, gifting him a magical amulet encrusted with diamonds and rubies.    Max was mesmerised by the amulet's radiance and felt a surge, nay, a force, run through his veins. With Star's gift, Max embarked on a journey to discover and unravel the mysteries of Jupitero. Traversing vibrant forests, iridescent lakes and vast seas, all teeming with exotic life. What more would he find?

The party comes across a cave of Crescent Dwarves in the side of the cliff. The dwarves inform the party of rhythmic chanting, thunderous noise, and screams of bliss coming from atop their mountain that shakes the dwarvesâ living space.    The mountain, Rapa Nui, has awakened. Its displeasure rumbles through the region and deep, rolling black smoke and chunks of fire explode from its head. The locals are panicked and there is no telling what they will do.    Two tribes of Jungle Giants, at peace after centuries of conflict, have built a âpeace bridgeâ spanning a huge canyon, and keep sentinels there to ensure the mutual trust between them. A cruising Roc, nearby, was the target of sport and thrown spears from the guards, as a laugh. The creature, enraged, destroyed the bridge and now both sides are blaming one another as war threatens to plunge the region into havoc again.

a man and a woman are in the jungle. there are there to study the lacal wildlife. one day they find a type of mushroom that has never been  seen before. they pic, and pacage up a few samples to take back with them.  after spending a few more days in the jungle they head back home. when they get home they begign to study the new mushroom. it is discouvered that the mushroom has great health beinfits. they become rich and famous from thier discovery.

A married couple and two cats decided to visit another planet. They researched the opportunities online and found the company which would take them to Saturn. Their preparations began by trying to float in the swimming pool and trying to hang upside down. They were just guessing the skills they would need to be okay on that journey and on that planet. The husband and wife were still waiting to receive the instructions from the company, but were both thrilled and nervous. The journey was about to happen in 1 month, but they were already telling their cats all about it. This adventure would be the only thing that would matter over the next weeks. Even the cats seemed to be excited!

Within the heart of an ancient abandoned jungle, an explorer called Robert was exploring this jungle which once had a many tribes on it. While exploring this jungle he found what was left of some of these tribes, abandoned huts, old fire places, and bones. He didn't know what could of caused all of the tribes to die out. As he was walking, Robert felt a strange presence in the jungle, he saw some footsteps going deep in the jungle.  He followed the footsteps until he found a temple which was build inside a mountain, He walked inside of the temple he saw 3 paths going into different directions, each of the paths were lit up by torches, he knew what that meant. Robert took the path that went straight, but said that these paths went extremely deep into the mountain, until he heard some sounds, that were of the remaining people of this jungle, he thought to himself that they might be the people that killed all the other tribes. Robert watched from away as the people were having their meal, when he stumbled and they heard him and turned around, He saw what looked to be the leader of the tribe walking towards him. Robert didn't try to run away but question the people to understand what was happening, the leader said that they didn't know about the other tribes being dead, and they were very friendly with him, they invited him to have his meal with them, and offered him to stay the night, he accepted the offer, he went to sleep, and after that the leader of the tribe killed him in his sleep.

One day a group of explorers decided to go to a different planet in the far reaches of space. the took plenty of supplies with them for the journey and set off. On arrival they discovered lots of new animals and plant life not found on earth and they were very excited about their discoveries. There were some very dangerous animals and poisonous plants they had to navigate around. Along the way they found some amazingly beautiful scenery which took their breath away, seas and mountains and even some extinct volcanos. The craft they had brought with them was running out of fuel so they decided to take cover in some sheltered tree type plants. Luckily there was another craft following them and it managed to land on the planet. Thankfully they rescued the group and took them back to earth.

The humans have finally colonised Mars!  Those who were fortunate to survive the journey, now have the weight of the unknown world on their shoulders.  There is no going back, their bravery is admired by those back home on Earth.  They must prepare the planet for future humans.  Can they discover the truth and prove there was once life on Mars?  Or are we going to learn that humans originate from the red planet?  Perhaps, life has never vanished and they are not alone?  Time will tell but until then, it's just them and the harsh environment without much support.

Our story today begins in the deep undergrown of the Indian jungle. Jeremiah, an explorer, from Brooklyn New York, is in stealth mode, for he has just spotted a rare tiger. This, the sabretooth spotted tiger, is going extinct and Jeremiah needs to seek information of the breed to save them. Jeremiah has been studying them now for eight years, along with his girlfriend, June. However, did I mention that Jeremiah is in fact scared of tigers?     Jeremiah doesn't know it yet, but he is brave, wise and very patient, the perfect concoction that the sabretooth spotted tigers need to survive. June knows this of course, but she isn't here yet to raise his morals. Let's see how our friend gets on.

Pete and Tim rented a boat to sail out to sea to look for treasure, armed with a map they boarded the boat with optimism that this could be their lucky day. They headed west to the coast and stumbled upon a cave. They slowly crept into the cave and brought the boat to a halt. They both stepped out onto the shore and began to explore. Tims torch happened upon something glistening in the sand so they hurried over with their spades and began to dig. A chest appeared before their eyes, excitedly they carried the chest back to the boat and gently prized it open. A wealth of treasure lit up their eyes as the lid opened, this WAS their lucky day! They turned the boat around and headed home, very pleased they took the risk and headed out onto the sea.

While exploring a newly discovered planet, a group of astronauts uncovers an ancient civilisation. The civilisation is full of mysterious technology and hidden chambers. As they delve deeper they find themselves unlocking the secrets of a powerful alien energy source that could revolutionise life on earth. This energy source resembles a beautiful red gemstone. The gemstone seems to entrance any human who gazes at it for too long and several members of the party are almost taken over by it. The astronauts must safely transport the source past strange flora and fauna back to their vessel. Once inside and on their return journey, the source begins to pulse and emits a whine which seems to cut through the crew's consciousness. The sound grows louder and louder and more unbearable the further the ship travels from the alien planet; will our heroes survive this otherworldly ordeal?

A group of e claimed explorers embark on the mission of a lifetime, all together, to explore a new planet with the main goal of investigating undiscovered lifeforms. The quest is an ambiguous one but they wish to uncover a sustained future for planet earth on another planet. They all are equipped with a unique area of expertise which is why they have been chosen for this mission by NASA. The groups thoughts and feelings towards the expedition are mixed but a common feeling is pride at NASA having the confidence in them and their knowledge in their field to select them for the mission. There have been some issues with group politics in the past as some members have come under fire for their ideas which have been dismissed by peer researchers. They must come together and work together for the greater good, harnessing their unique knowledge for the good of earth and all man kind. NASA nervously awaits descent after 10 years of planning, careful selection and training. It should be noted that the rest of the world also watch in anticipation and awe of the crew.

Jake had never even seen the sea before. In the eight short years of his life, all he had known was his modest village upbringing. But today, with fresh memories of his home burning to ash, he awoke to the sounds of water sloshing against the walls and uneasiness under his feet. The ground had never swayed before. Clinging to the walls for support, he traced along metallic walkways and footwells in search of something familiar. After an hour of searching around - there - standing overlooking the vast emptiness of his now blue world, his mother. She picks him up into her arms as she turns him to face what she calls the ocean, their new home. At least, until it is safe to return - if it ever will be.

In a perilous journey on the open seas, a crew of daring adventures embark on a dangerous quest to discover uncharted territories. Along the way, they encounter mystifying legends, formidable foes, and stunning natural wonders. The crew must rely on their courage, friendship and unbreakable determination to prevail, forging unforgettable bonds while leaving a lasting mark on the world around them.   Along the journey, a slogan goes on to say: "I will find the one piece!" With this, the crew determined to train. With this training, they grew stronger. And as they grew stronger, they became more competent in fighting. And as they became more competent in fighting, they became confident in every aspect of their skill-base.

A group of friends decided to go on a daring jungle adventure to find a missing airplane that crashed that contained many mysteries.  The journey through the jungle led to many different experiences. One person struggled with food poisoning whilst another person had a twisted ankle from tripping over. Despite this they all still ventured deeper and deeper. As the friends got closer they heard weird noises coming from the area where the plane crashed. Slowly they got closer and closer. When they got to the aircraft they were shocked at what they saw. The friends haven't been heard from since.

There is life from the outer space. At thousands light-year from Earth on planet Gamma, a humanoid civilisation is living in harmony. They are very advanced and evolved both emotionally and technologically. With their supercars (flying vehicle, which can travel the galaxy through teleportation), they can visit all parts of the universe while staying connected with each other. This is such an ancient civilisation ( approximately 2 millions year of existence ), this is why they already learnt to deal with the negative impact of toxic thoughts and emotions. As a result and reward for their good deeds, they can live today in perfect peace and harmony with their environment. I figured out I got so much to learn from them, that even a lifetime wouldn't be enough. I need to stay on this planet a little longer now .

Jim, Sam and Coty hadn't expected much from this Summer break - plans had fallen through and the eight weeks that lay before them seemed like forever.  It wasn't until the day that changed everything for them that things took a turn for the more exciting.  On July 29th the three friends embarked on a thrilling adventure into the depths of a jungle - thanks mainly to the unexpected generosity of a long lost relative of Coty's who had sent them a mysterious letter.  Within the letter were three tickets to the jungle. Deep in the jungle they encountered exotic wildlife and were forced to navigate through challenging landscapes. Along the way, their journey led them through an ancient lost city, hidden beneath thick, dark foliage where they had no choice but to try and solve mysterious puzzles in order to uncover the city's secrets.  The seemingly dull and tedious eight week break ended up being far from that.  One the 22nd day in the jungle a helicopter arrived to pick up the three friends - piloted by the mysterious relative who explained that they had simply wished for Coty to experience the joys of the jungle and find priceless treasures away from the chaos of modern life.

I was deep in the emerald jungle. Only armed with courage and my fists. My senses were heightened by the sounds of a lion's roar. The sound echoed through the jungle, seeming to come from all directions. The air was heavy, making it hard to breathe, it was weighing me down and carrying the roar of the lion. Momentarily spellbound by the roar, I managed to gain the use of my legs and run. Unfortunately the thick jungle caused me to slip. Then i fell, looking up to be eye to eye with the lion.

The plant Zogg was a unique a mysterious place far far away. A group of young explorers have ventured a long way to discover what lies on this mysterious planet. They were in awe when they discovered tropical waters and flowers like a planet of paradise. To their surprise they were not the only living creatures currently on this plant, it's resident aliens of adult zoggers and children called the zoggetts lived their lives up here. Most of them seemed friendly but it certainly was hard for them to adjust, many of them wished they could stay and live there. The group worried if they went back home and told people on earth that they would invade and take over the planet. This would mean the beauty and paradise of Zogg would be taken from the aliens. The group decided this would be their secret, the Zoggers and Zoggetts loved the group so much they were allowed to come and visit as much as they want whenever they want and they would never tell another person.
its a glorious day out at sea.  All around nothing but water.  my boat is small.  its starts to wobble.  its filling up with water.  I think I'm sinking.  I've cut myself.   I see a fin.

Once upon a time, there were four friends named Alex, Ben, Chloe and Daisy. They were all super excited to go on an adventure in the jungle. They packed their backpacks with snacks, water and a map. As they walked through the dense forest they heard strange noises which made their hearts start to race. Suddenly, they stumbled upon a hidden temple covered in vines. With curiosity in their eyes, they entered the mysterious temple. Inside they found a golden statue with treasure surrounding it. But as they reached out to touch it, the ground started to shake and the temple collapsed, burying them alive.

He dropped the anchor and left behind the family he loved.  He had to see what was out there.  Did the gold really exist and did he have the ability to find it? John sailed for weeks to the area he believed it had been buried and was proud when he got there.  He equipped himself with his scuba gear and dived down to the depths of the ocean. It was murky and black but the gold shone out like a spotlight on a singer.  John grabbed everything he could and made his way back to the ship each time with a huge grin on his face.  He sailed back home and his family were waiting on the dock for him with beaming faces not sure if they were happier to see John safely return or the huge pile of gold that filled his ship.

We last saw our plane three days ago, when we crashed through the dense jungle foliage 150 miles from our destination. Since then I and my two friends have been trekking through the uncharted landscape, heat and humidity driving us mad, fierce wild animals a threat we all fear round every twisting tree and tangled vine. Nightfall draws near, and it's then that our luck seems to change; in the distance a gentle glowing light shines through the emerald leaves, and with the last of our energy we stumble towards it. What greets us as we part through the thinning jungle is a settlement, an indigenous village we'd never even heard of, people appearing one by one from their woven wooden homes to investigate our arrival. We tense, my friend reaching for something in his backpack but I stay his hand. Only when the people seem appeased can we finally draw our next calm breath - and our pacificity had been worth it. Through jumbled signs and gestures that last through much of the evening, we finally communicate our troubles, and the people begin to point all in one direction, East of here, and following their guidance we make it back to recognised civilisation. For the rest of our lives not one of us shared a word of the people who saved us, not daring to bring the horrors of modernity down upon their peaceful village.

I've always wanted to partake in an adventure on the open seas and surprisingly the opportunity arose just last year. I'd booked and embarked a fairly bog standard 2 week sailing holiday touring the Greek Islands during the summer months last year. There was myself and 5 other guests on the boat together with the captain and two other crew members responsible for the day to day running of the boat and keeping their paying passengers happy. All was proceeding as planned and we'd already enjoyed some leisurely sailing initially setting sail from Athens and touring the Greek mainland coast two days and two nights before heading into more adventurous waters. The plan was to head toward Santorini and we were well on our way until the fourth night of the trip where we encountered the most amazing an colourful storm the like of which I have never seen before. As we were engulfed by the storm the boat was lifted out of the water and we found ourselves bashed and buffeted towards an island which worryingly the captain informed us did not appear on any maps and to make matters worse the storm had made out boat no longer seaworthy and knocked out all of our communications and navigation equipment. We set up camp on the island as best we could with what we could extract from our damaged boat but what was even stranger we were not alone on the island - it would appear that we were sharing the island with a colony of 6 foot tall chickens. So we're still there now three months later but things have not been too bad with a plentiful supply of massive eggs but I'm afraid we're all starting to get very sick of the meals consisting of mainly omelette and scrambled eggs to the quicker you can rescue us from where we've ended up as a result of our open seas adventure I'd be extremely grateful!

Sophie stared at the computer. Back 'home', summers had been marked by the constant swatting of tiny flies which seemed to have each have the personal goal of ruining her peace as she typed. Here, a pervasive stillness surrounded her instead - no bugs, no life. Only the computer's thrum accompanied her thoughts as she put them to paper, her experience thus far on Higaldy Pigaldy Base 5. Three months had passed since her arrival on planet, since she permanently said goodbye to all she knew back on Earth. Tomorrow, she would finally be setting off in the ship which would slingshot her across the stars, so she could document her journey to fans back on Earth. Though she would never go back, her role was integral in reporting humankind's continued cross-galaxy missions back to those who only heard about it through weekly reports. Sophie was excited about this new life she was beginning, but as she continued to stare at the empty document, she couldn't seem to stop thinking about those flies.

One day i sailed with a boat into the deep blue sea. I saw a shark and panicked. I tried to sail back but my daughter was fascinated with the shark. So i waited for some time to see if the shark would circle back to the island. We did not have much food only a few crackers. My daughter was so small she started throwing crackers into the sea. I panicked even more thinking the shark would come back to eat us. After some time the shark disappeared we were relieved and sailed back to the island.

Velma and Tom had arrived in Bolivia on the eve of a riotous election cycle. Seeing that it was safer to venture into the jungle, the two drove through until their car broke down. Panicking, Velma attempted to change the wheel, in the hopes of being able to drive off as soon as possible. At this point, Tom spotted a rare bird flying around the trees. Seeking to take note of the bird for his bird watching book, Tom wondered off into the jungle, goading Velma into going with him. Whilst trying to keep pace with the bird, the two found a lake with a broken down car. The two worked on prying the wheel from out of the wreckage, when the bird swooped down and stole Tom's hat. Tom then chased after the bird, leaving Velma alone to carry the wheel back to the car.

This is the story of a female Pirate, one that time and the history books seem to have forgotten. Follow Kira's trilling adventures across the open seas. Hear her about her trials and tribulations facing storms, encounters with sea creatures real and mythical. She how she unearths hidden treasure in exotic lands, and societies, making both friends and enemies along the way. See how she uses her wit, courage, and intelligence to outwit those who would try and thwart her plans and ambitions. And. of course, follow her as she falls in love with the man of her dreams. follow their adventures, and challenges all the way to old age.

The sea was calm and the waves were crashing against the hull of the ship, being on the open sea was always something that Captain Joe had enjoyed. As a pirate, he had seen his fair share of adventures, but nothing seemed to be as important as the journey he was embarking on at that moment. The quest to find the fabled grail of riches had always been at the forefront of his mind, something that he hadn't been able to forget ever since he had heard the story when he was a small boy.   Joe couldn't help but smile as he cast his gaze over the open sea, his crew diligently going about their duties. He had been waiting his entire life for this moment. Taking off his hat, he leaned against the ships wheel and breathed in deeply, indulging himself in the crisp sea air that surrounded him. He tried to put out of his mind the fact that the authorities were no doubt looking for their ship, ready and waiting to arrest him for piracy. They hadn't caught him yet and he intended to keep it that way.

My friend and I decided to go a short day cruise to explore the coves of this beautiful island.  It was a day trip but the actual destination was unknow to us and would be a real surprise.  We sailed early in the morning and were able to enjoy the sunrise above the horizon.  What a beautiful scene it was   The boat was followed by jumping fish which accompanied us on this discovery trip.  When we finally arrived, we were in a lagoon amongst crystal clear water surrounded by high cliffs offering their shade.  We could see a multitude of colourful fish which seeemed undisturbed by our presence.  Everybody stayed quite for a while appreciating the beauty and peacefullness of this moment.  Could this be the paradise ?

Will and Emma's boat crashed ashore, breaking into hundreds of pieces as it smashed against the rocks. They had gone off course during their round the world challenge, had no idea where they were, and beyond the small, rocky beach they had touched down on, all they could see in both directions was a wall of tall, thick trees. It was beginning to get dark and they needed to seek help, if not, shelter. Will and Emma entered the jungle, holding each others' hands tightly, and after a few minutes of walking, a bright light started to appear from among the vine-covered trees. They headed towards the light, despite being unsure of what it was - they hoped it would be a place of sanctuary where they would find help or, at the very least, a place to stay the night. As they edged closer, many sounds echoed around them - buzzes, roars, and the screams of primates. Will and Emma picked up their pace until they were face to face with what was creating the light, where they found, to their surprise, nothing but an ancient, freestanding door. Should they open it?

Once uopn a time there were three young boys. Alan Brian and Jo. They were all in the same class at school and they were all 14 years old. Alan had a great idea, one day that they should travel to have an adventure in the jungle. They would pack a picnic and take their bikes. The jungle wasn't far from the school and no one would notice they weren't there for the day. They all got up very early and travelled the short distance. The jungle was here, they entered into the leafy green abyss and started their adventure.

A courageous captain and his 8 men crew members embarked on an audacious journey across the most dangerous waters in search of a long lost kings treasure. They encountered a lot of weird unseen sea creatures and cunning rival pirates, but they were determined to get to their destination and didn't return back to their base despite the challenges faced on their way. In the middle of the ocean they faced a locked gate which required a key which they were not in possession of, after so much brain storming they joined ties with the evil pirates form another titan ship so as to get the key but the pirates wanted a grand payment from them which was to take the glory of finding the treasure and take out of the gold in the box. The story culminates in both triumph and tragedy as they uncover the coveted treasure while forging bonds that transcend social barriers and create lifelong friendships. unfortunately, the engine of their great ship malfunctioned and that caused the ship to sink and they all had to scamper for safety which meant they never got to uncover the kings treasure. They eventually got into another tiny boat that took them back to shore the captain advised them to the ocean. They all decided to go together and restrategise on new ways to accomplish mission. they packed all necessary amenities and began journey of which they were eventually successful.

A group of thrill-seekers embark on an fuelled adventure in the heart of the jungle.They  encountered exotic creatures. They overcame the challenges of the untamed wild. As they navigate through the lush foliage, they unravel a long-lost mystery of an ancient civilisation and its hidden treasures. When faced with decision to reveal their discovery to the world or preserve the secrets of the jungle, they must confront their own inner struggles. They allow the magic of the wild to guide their hearts. As they walked in deep in the dark wild, the mystery of the deep dark jungle got more complicated. They started to explore the tracks and find out more about the animals in the wild.

The spacecraft landed more smoothly than expected on the newly discovered planet known only as Planet Z. The astronauts were cautious at first, using the external cameras on the spacecraft to assess the outdoor landscape. There did not appear to be any life on planet Z, just miles and miles of grey sandy land. Once they deemed there new surroundings to be safe it was decided it was time to depart the spacecraft and begin exploring planet Z for the first time. The astronauts stayed within close proximity of the spacecraft to ensure they had a constant supply of oxygen and in case of any danger. This was a new expedition with little known about the planet so caution was a must. The astronauts collected samples of the sandy ground, took temperature readings and photographs of the landscape before returning to the spaceship. Two days later the spaceship returned safely to planet earth.

Three daring friends embark on a thrilling adventure through the heart of the jungle. They go deep into the jungle to try to find a good camping spot. But on the way they encounter a another group that is already at the spot they want to camp. Before they knew it the other group got confrontational and start to have a go at them with unkind words. So they decide it would be best to vacate the area and find another spot. They continue on they way and come across a cave with a overhang and think that would be a good spot, they then start setting up they tent. Then they decide what to eat but find they need water to cook they food. But no one would go get the water until Joseph volunteered to go get it, and while he was they he found some bananas which he shared with the group when he got back to the camping spot and the other people was very grateful and thanked him.

This is a story about three young astronauts named Stevie, Helen and John who embarked on a journey together to a distant, uncharted planet. The three siblings were sleeping one night when they were woken by a strange high pitched sound and bright light. At first they were paralysed with fear, but Stevie, the oldest and most curious of the group decided to go outside to investigate. In the back garden Stevie met an Alien being without a name who offered to take Stevie and his brother and sister back to its home planet. Stevie had always wanted to explore space and ran back inside to persuade Helen and John to join him on the voyage. They flew for many Earth hours to the faraway plant of Zoog and were given a guided tour of the planet. The whole planet was covered in different coloured clouds, and beautiful bird-like animals flew around making strange noises. After the three humans had admired the beauty of the planet, the alien flew them back to Earth and they were back in time for school the next morning.

The village was like a timewarp - Like looking into the past, but with an unusual twist. Everything was different. Houses where upside down, with the roof at the bottom and the door at the top, with no clear or visible way to get in. The villagers were friendly, but we could not understand them, nor they us. They were fascinated by us, our style, our equipment, and our overall look. With nowhere for us to stay, we tried to leave, but could not. Every time we left through the trees, via the same way we arrived, we ended up in the village again. We quickly realised that all was not as it seemed, and upon nightfall, things became very different.

It was a wonderful sunny day on the south coast. Paul and his friend decided to go out to sea in a boat. The journey started of well, on a nice calm ocean. But as they day went on, the weather took a turn. It started to get  windy. The boat began to rock, and water was entering the boat. Paul tried to turn the boat to steer it back to shore. But it was extremely difficult in the wind. Just as it started to turn, the wind dropped and the sun came out again and all was calm at sea

An explorer embarks on a journey through an uncharted jungle, confident and curious, they have a desire to uncover its hidden mysteries. It is told there is all sorts of undiscovered finds in the massive jungle and the explorer intends to unravel it. Along the way, they forge unexpected alliance with the diverse creatures inhabiting the tropical landscape and uncover ancient ruins filled with lost treasures and ornaments. The explorer enjoyed the company of apes, snakes, and other unlikely strangers. It is a story that is unlikely to be believed.  Through perseverance, the explorer ultimately uncovers the secrets of the jungle and returns home with tales of adventure, inspiring others to seek out their own extraordinary experiences. Maybe one day others will be with the animals too. Maybe one day, they will feel fulfilled.

Three brave astronauts embark on a thrilling journey to explore an uncharted planet. They unearth a hidden alien civilization, rich in resources and advanced technology. Navigating through dangerous challenges, they ultimately build an alliance with the extra terrestrial species. The astronauts decide to contact Earth and suggest they send more rockets and people so that they can set up a base on the planet. Earth are unsure whether its safe and are worried the aliens might change their mind and become unfriendly if we start moving more humans to the planet. But the astronauts are insistent that they are friendly and that starting a camp here will be good for the future of both planets. So earth finally agree and send another 5 rockets with people and equipment to build a camp and try to start a new joint civilization. The new people will become pioneers and will live and work side by side with the aliens sharing their knowledge of each others planets and technology for a better life.

A trawler boat sets sail for the open seas in search for some big fish. They reach there location in the deep north sea and cast there nets. The next thing they know, there boat is being dragged around viciously and they end up being dragged under the deep dark sea with no idea what is causing this disaster. One sailer seas a glimpse of a giant creature with big black eyes. The creature swollows the crew one by one and tears the boat to pieces. The sailors are now in the creatures stomach, but to there surprise they are unharmed and there is no water inside the stomach, they can breath. They start to plan an escape, but have no idea of what to do, so they sit and wait. 24 hours later they are spat out of the creatures mouth and land upon a beach, they are in complete paradise, alnd full of fruit and golden beaches.

A bunch of young teenagers were about to set out on a journey across the islands. They were accompanied by the ships captain and three members of the crew. As they departed from port, jacob and sarah the siblings who arranged the journey realised that Adam seemed to be absent from the ship. The ships captain, captain Smith set off anyways on the journey from the north island to the south island. Ten minutes into the journey, panic set in to the teenagers as they realised they couldnt find Adam. The frantic search began to find Adam, as the teenagers searched the entire ship the weather was causing the sea to throw the ship from side to side. As they looked out in the direction they came from they realised that Adam had slipped over board. Acting on instinct Jacob and Sarah quickly grabbed a rope and with the help of the rest of the group, threw it over the side for Adam to grab on to and be pulled back aboard.

The rocket landed on the mysterious and potentially uninhabited planet. The diverse alien landscape gave off a greenish glow as though it were alive. The ground was soft but undulating under their feet as they stepped out and into the unknown. Above their heads was an aurora never seen on Earth. It weaved an orange ribbon through the sky as though motioning them towards something ahead. A noise could be heard but it was hard to tell where it was coming from as they wandered through the glowing desert towards dark silhouettes. Hearts beating loudly under their suits almost creating panic within them. The silhouettes reavealed themselves lit by the aurora.

In a time when space travel has advanced above todays standards, three astronauts exploring space find themselves on a strange new planet. The planet they find themselves on is very different from earth and is very beautiful to see. As they continue to explore the planet they find themselves amongst new strange creatures and a eco system that is completely foreign. They attempt to talk to the these creatures and find a way to communicate with them. They appear friendly and are interested in where they are from and what it is like. After a series of conversations with these creatures a bond is created. The astrounauts end up forming an alliance with the earthlings. They promise to share their techonology and understanding of the universe as long as we do the same.

The plane crash landed in the heart of the jungle, the survivors gathered their thoughts and exited the craft as quickly as they could. Upon exiting the plane they were careful to find their feet as they navigated the uneven terrain. The group quickly spotted that there was a clearing up ahead and decided to head in that direction in the hope of finding civilisation. Gathering what resources they could they ensured they had radios, food, water and any first aid equipment they could find, they set off in hopes of finding help. Laura, the pilot decided to take charge and lead the way, she had experienced the jungle before so had some idea of what to expect, her first hurdle was to work their way around the wildlife and potentially poisonous plants they may encounter. As the group progressed the trees began to thin out and they could see that the sun was begining to set, the group knew they needed to hurry as noone wanted to spend the night in the jungle. After a few hours of trekking the radio came to life and voices could be heard, the group were estatic at the thought of being rescued. After identifying their location a helicopter was on its way to them and the team were rescued.

In a hot and humid summer, our family decided to go on a jungle holiday.   We are very excited and really looking forward to this adventure together.   We landed and met our guide at the airport. Our adventure begins.   He called John and he is very experienced about this land.  He took us to the jungle in his jeep which was very exciting.   We saw a herd of buffalos just chilling out.   We also saw some zebras.

I arrived, with a crew of eight, on planet Zog after a long journey in our time machine. When we left my machine miraculously I found that we could breathe normally.  We started to explore and discovered a strange creature, like a bear but also different from anything encountered on earth.  The creature was clearly amazed by our appearance on Zog but seemed friendly.  The bear-like creature signalled for us to follow, taking as to a large bright cave surrounded by colourful flowers and plantation.  He took us to a group of similarly amazing creatures, who wanted us to eat.  The food was fantastic, although we were cautious, it was certainly safe to eat; this is paradise - we'll certainly stay, will be an education all round..

Amidst the ruins of an ancient civilization, two astronauts explore the lush and enigmatic planet of Zarmina, hoping to uncover the reasons behind the extinction of its inhabitants. Harry was the commander and was joined by Captain Smith. They encounter peculiar creatures, unique flora, and the remanants of advanced technology that could change the future of humanity. As they piece together the mystery, their lives are transformed by the planet's mystical secrets, leaving them forever changed. There bodies had started to adapt to the terrain.  Harry developed gills and webbed feet, allowing him speed and grace to cross the various lakes they encountered. He did struggle to breath when on land which seemed to be a side effect of his new predicament. Meanwhile Captain Smith was growing taller, not that it was noticable at first.

The crew were a rowdy lot all 23 of them. They did the work that the captain gave them which included cleaning the deck, steering the ship, navigating the ship using the stars at night. The ships crew would always be on the look out for other ships to rob of supplies like food, water and gold. They would also be on the look out for islands for a place to rest and restock supplies. The ship was an old looking ship by the name of Angel of Doom. It had a carved big colourful lady on the front with long brown hair and blue eyes. The captain was called Henry Vane but his real name was William Butterworth. They had been at sea for three months without coming across another ship and their supplies were running low.

As Sam is walking through the dense, hot and humid jungle, she can feel the stickiness of the air grasp onto her skin with sweat dripping down. She is still searching for a way out.. as she treks on she hears rustling behind her. Frozen, Knife ready down by her side in case anything comes out and attacks her, as she slowly walks away.. a few seconds later a lion suddenly leaps from the big green brushes and ready to take a bite. Sam immediately swings her knife and slices the lion's throat causing it to wallow and scream, and runs away.

They first became aware that all was not right when they heard a strange noise. It boomed around the ruins causing them to stop. They listened and looked at each other. The noise sounded again, louder this time. Some of the adventures took out sticks and knives and grouped together. The noise was coming from the far right corner. Suddenly the booking stopped and a thump thump sound started. Then out of the corner came the biggest scariest thing they had ever seen.

Jonah, a budding archaeologist, discovered an ancient map hidden away in a locked safe belonging to his late father. With no hesitation, Jonah contacted three of his friends and off they went to embark on an adrenaline-fueled adventure in the heart of an amazonian jungle. After fours days of travel in the scorching heat by mix of plane, boat and foot the four friends finally arrived at the coast near the jungles outer edges. Despite, it's mythical aura and tranquil views, the locals warned of a great danger that lurks in the jungle. Jonah, unfazed as he had heard similar stories countless times before wanting to head straight into the jungle. Jared, on the other hand, felt unnerved and claimed he could sense an evil presence radiating from the jungle, despite his reservations, Jared did not want to disappoint his long time friend and ventured into the jungle with the rest of his team. After a days walk and camp, they followed the map to a clearing in the jungle, Jonah angrily kicked and stomped the guard in frustration, insisting he had followed the map correctly, as he continued to stomp, the ground began to give way and he disappeared from sight as he fell into the temple below. Fortunately, decades of vegetation broke Jonah's fell, looking around Jonah quickly released this was no temple but it was a tomb, slowly walking closer to one of the vastly decayed bodies, Jonah looked at an elegant medallion placed upon the body; suddenly the hand grabbed Jonah by the throat and with it's empty facial sockets, gazed into Jonah's eyes, emitting a purple glow that allowed it's spirit to possess Jonah, unleashing an ancient evil into the world.

Captain Stormright planned to gather as much treasure from the deserted ship as he could,  He thought of how the treasure could help him to become the richest pirate in all the seven seas,  he ordered his minions to board the ship and fill all their sacks with the many untold riches. Little did Stromright know, the ship was boobytrapped to the high heavens. As his minions mounted the deserted ship, the events of horror began to enford.  Peg-leg Smith was hoisted upside down by his feet and catapulted into the air by a hoist mechanism, Bucktooth Jack was peppered with metal shards that instantly ceased his existence and the other 6 members of Stormwrights band of unfortunate souls succumbed to trap doors that dropped them into pits filled with flesh eating crustaceans. Stormwright watched from afar on his own ship, he was a feared man but certainly not a brave one. His personal ship, the 'Wooden Barnacle' was his safe haven but without the men to help him tarverse he was stuck in this in the middle of the pacific ocean, alone and afraid. He had no intention of going to try to save his men on the ship that he foreseen to make all his dreams come true. He was stuck, he would run out of food and water in the next few days and no sailor in their right mind would attempt to save men on a reknowned pirate vessel, nautical karma.

Jim and Clive had always wanted to go for an adventure in the Amazon rainforest, it had been their dream since they were 5 years old. After saving up the money while working at university they decided to go once they'd finished their studies. They flew to Rio de Janerio at the start of summer to begin their adventure, but they had no idea how much of an adventure it would turn out to be.     After a few days trekking in jungle they started to hear some strange noises at night, for the first couple of nights it sounded quite far away but gradually the sounds got closer and closer. It started to worry Jim but Clive was unfazed by the noises, he just thought they were harmless animals. Soon they'd find out that Clive couldn't have been more wrong.    One night Jim woke with a start, he was sure he had felt something touch his foot, he looked at their tent's entrance but there was nothing there. Just before he rolled over and went back to sleep he glanced at Clive's sleeping bag, but it wasn't there.

Catherine turned over in bed and fell and fell and fell for what seemed like forever until, with a thump, she landed on a bed of wet leaves. It was her favourite dream, the jungle dream: a private and unending landscape of tall, wide trees, vines and the cacophany of tropical birds. She had been visiting in her dreams since she was a child, and now she was very familiar with it. She walked through the jungle unafraid and playful, holding out her arms for the birds that came to perch on her elbow. The jungle was endless and it never changed, except - except - who was that? A boy rather older than her walked through the jungle ahead of her, and he jumped when she called out in excitement.   'Who are you - what's your name?'   'Why should I tell you,' said the boy, 'since you are only a dream in my head?'

The journey there took an awfully long time.  In fact, it took light years.  And I'm not even sure how long a light year takes, but they seem to go on forever!  But when we arrived, this planet was out of this world...quite literally!  It was unlike anything I've experienced on Earth, and although it was exciting, I was extremely nervous.

Dr Steven was a world renowned explorer. His lifelong ambition was to discover a new uninhabited land mass. He packed his equipment and supplies onto a small fishing trawler he had purachsed from fish face Dave. He set sail on a dull and windy day with hopes higher than the biggest of waves. Steve lasted 30 minutes before he realised he had forgotten his phone and had to return back to shore. He finally set out 3 hours later already feeling exhausted. The trawler was old but built to last and saw him safely through the first stage of his journey. His true adverturem was still to get underway.

On arrival, Fazziel and the others had been astonished by the uncanny strangeness of the sky with its odd green tinge, and the three suns. The interweaving cycles of Short Day and Long Day and Night had played havoc with their sleep patterns. Without the welcoming, gentle  diplomacy of the Blue People. they were sure they would have fallen foul of the more belligerent inhabitants, in their weakened and confused state. As things had progressed toward what they now thought of as the "new normal" of life on the planet, it gradually, though slowly, became apparent that there were complications in the relations between the different sentient species, which they would never fully understand, and must be very careful to tread around. This, of course, is to be expected in all first contact scenarios, and was a major focus of their training, but it is recognised that the particular nuances of a given situation can never be foreseen, or fully comprehended, Caution and humility are absolutely crucial, and yet, in spite of meticulous training and selection of participants, unpredictable difficulties always arise.     Thus, I could not be surprised to learn of the perilous conditions which had developed over the course of that first World-Year (which I must remind you, is equivalent to almost three Earth-years); on the contrary, I must commend the unit for the tenacity and astuteness with which they were able to navigate the relationships, such that there is now a flourishing and mutually beneficial alliance between the parties. The peaceful conditions which now prevail have enabled the unit to pursue their research and develop a broader knowledge of the various inhabitants, which I shall describe in as much detail as possible in this report.

I went on a trip to the rainforest in Kakadu, as close to the jungle as you will ever get in Australia. We slept or were meant to sleep in a big open tent with mosquito nets to keep the bugs out.  You had a choice - sleep on the bottom bunk or sleep on the top bunk. If you slept on the top bunk you got the spiders. If you slept on the bottom bunk you got the rats. I chose the top bunk. It's always amazed me how people can sleep in such conditions. I never sleep at times like that, and especially not after one moment in the night when someone shone a torch into the tent, and I could see above me, sitting quietly, a spider as big as my hand.

The submarine descended into the depths of the Mariana Trench, its steel exterior withstanding the immense pressure.  The crew's excitement was palpable as they navigated through the mysterious darkness, guided by their instruments and unwavering curiosity. In the abyssal plain, they encountered bioluminescent creatures, illuminating the darkness with their ethereal glow. The trench's immensity was humbling, its depths unknown and unexplored. In the mesmerizing world of the trench, they discovered unique species adapted to survive in extreme conditions, unlocking secrets of evolution. With every observation and sample collected, they pieced together the complex puzzle of this hidden realm. With their mission complete, they resurfaced, carrying with them a wealth of knowledge and a newfound appreciation for the mysteries of the deep. Their journey had revealed not only the wonders of the Mariana Trench but also the boundless potential of human exploration and the unquenchable thirst for knowledge that drives us to the unknown.

The island slowly came into view as the friends sailed towards it. They and their ship had survived so much to reach this point. They had navigated treacherous waters. They had battled sea monsters. They had overcome pirates. All in their quest to uncover the island's secrets and they were finally within reach of their goal. The island proved light work compared to everything the friends had endured to reach it. They sailed away with the treasure, newfound wisdom, and everlasting bonds.

After finding a big hole in a tree, a group of explorers found there way teleported to a new alien world. This world was full of strange plants and landscapes, and they couldn't figure out why they were there or how to get home. They began to befriend the animals of the planet until they found animals that were not so friendly. During their travels they began to learn lessons on trust, loyalty, and courage. One of the explorers got injured along the journey, of which a human like creature appeared and healed them. The creature could speak through their minds so they could understand it, and it told them stories of the history of the planet. They explained of the bad creatures they didn't get along with, and how these tried to get rid of their species. The explorers worked alongside them to aid the creature, but with an ending twist finding out they were bad.

This planet is not like Earth, and the inhabitants are not human - they are similar to us but they don't understand our language, nor do they communicate via human means. They are friendly and receptive, and eager to learn how we can share our knowledge - we both make efforts to communicate and progress is being made, slowly. So far, we've been able to share and understand how humans live on earth, how and why we arrived on their planet and most importantly, share and understand that both us humans and aliens are friendly and able to coexist. Much can be learned from both sides; we have so far learned that the aliens are also travellers and do not normally reside on this planet, but they are far better space travellers than us humans, having seen many different worlds and galaxies. We are able to share this with Earth and provide knowledge on other parts of the galaxy that we have not been able to visit, yet alone comprehend. The aliens are fascinated, apparently, by our rudimentary forms of travel and the requirements for us to use Earth's natural resources. We have learned much more than the aliens have learned from us - we can now harness power from alternative sources which means we don't have to rely on burning fossil fuels. This has improved Earth's chances of future survival, and an allegiance has formed between the aliens and the human race to exchange cultural information and knowledge.

Last summer I went to the jungle in the amazon rainforest. Joining me was my wife, and all we brought was a backpack and some explorer equipment. Some of the equipment was detrimental for survival, such as a water filter, it was necessary because there was no other source of water. I took an extendable fishing rod that I bought on amazon, it was great because it fit inside of my backpack. The first night was awesome, we hiked a lot, saw so many extraordinary creatures and set up the tent for the night. The second day though, was not as nice. The rain made all of our clothes and equipment completely wet and we were starting to get hungry. I got my fishing rod and some bait and tried to catch a fish, fishes hate the rain and i was not able to catch anything during the entire day, we went to sleep starving.

I woke up. I was on a boat in the sea and it was freezing outside. It smelt of fish and beer and sea-sickness. I was stranded for 9 months. The rocking of the boat made me dizzy and the hard floor I woke up on caused me back pains. I stood up holding the edge of the boat for support. I heard sea gulls calling in the distance. I want to go back home.

The dense jungle was thick with the sound of howling monkeys and chirping insects. The travellers were coming up to the river they had seen on the map, crossing it would lead them even closer to the treasure. As they were about to cross, a crocodile emerged from the depths and snapped its sharp teeth together menacingly. The couple decided to walk the edge a while, in hopes of finding an easy and safer route across. About a mile down the path and half an hour later they came across a low hanging vine. It looked sturdy and the pair agreed to take it in turns to swing across. The man went first, testing out the strength by tugging on it first, took a big leap and glided over the river. With a thump, he landed on the other side with ease and threw the vine over to his partner, smiling.

Four travellers from earth crash land on a unkown distant planet.  The sky is green and the water from a nearby sea is purple.  Their main aim is to find a fuel source and repair their crashed shuttle.  Suddenly an unknown type of craft enters their view and they prepare for first contact.  The aliens appear and look intimidating at first being 8ft tall but you then hear a voice in your head.  "Do not fear us " they say "we are here to help" and they produce a holomap of the planet.  After two days journey you come across a well of dark matter that can power their shuttle.  After two days repair work the shuttle is repaired and Earth has made a new ally and is no longer alone in the universe.

Laura had never been invited on her parent's frequent exploration trips before, so when they asked her if she would like to come to Madagascar with them, she was nervous and excited all at once. Soon after settling in her temporary home, Laura packed her hiking sack and head off with her father, a local ranger - Timun - and his friendly dog, Pal. It wasn't long before the heat, the moisture and the constant exercise sapped Laura's energy and she found herself flagging behind Timun and her dad, but Pal kept her company. She stopped for a drink, loosening her flask lid and chugging down water relishing the cool hitting her throat. Wiping away the excess that she'd dribbled on her lips with the back of her hand, she realised she could no longer hear the footsteps of Timun and her father. "Dad?" she called, "DAD!" But there was no reply.

Two adventurous astronauts travelled to the unexplored planet named Fluto in the newest Rocket 365. They had been planning this trip for so long and were beyond excited to see what they would find there. The uneventful journey took a little over two days to reach Fluto and went exactly as planned and to schedule, hopefully a sign of good things to come. When they landed on the centre of Fluto, the astronauts wasted no time in stepping out of Rocket 365. They couldn't believe their eyes as the door opened. It was the most beautiful, bright and colourful place they had ever seen. They instantly felt so happy and the vibe and atmosphere was just the most positively indescribable feeling. They knew then that they had stumbled across something really incredible and this was the start of a very exciting story.

All of us dream of making great riches. One young chap heard of a city in a far away land filled with gold and gemstones. Nightly he dreamt of passage to this country of plenty. His thoughts became all consuming. Thus, a voyage across the Atlantic became at once necessary. An adventure on the open seas awaits. To the docks, he departed. Procurement of a suitable vessel, his only goal.

Her first step out of the landing craft was not as she'd envisaged. Three mind-numbingly long years of travel, trapped on 'Mission Zero' with five of the dumbest, most infuriating excuses for humans she could have imagined, and this moment had been so long-awaited. Yet, in the short seconds of what should have been a europhoric moment, her mind was filled with the mundane. Would her boots leak, and why hadn't she chosen porridge rather than boiled egg for breakfast? She blinked into the light of the three suns now peeking over the mountainous horizon. What should she say on the intercom, to record this moment for humankind? Something obvious about the beauty of the landscape? Or maybe just honesty: she missed home.

The Vanish, the worlds most famous exploration ship, was 20 days into its latest voyage to find a missing crew when it was beset by a devastating storm in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. The brave captain tried to keep the Vanish afloat for as long as possible, yet unfortunately the storm was too severe and the ship capsized with the survivors of the wreck desperately trying to survive aboard the small lifeboats. After a day and a half at sea, the lifeboats drifted towards a tropical island and the captain and his crew disembarked to make a camp at the beach and await rescue. However, as the sun rose each day, the crew noticed that one of their number went missing. Efforts were made to locate the missing crew members, yet there were no signs of footprints or tracks leading away from their camp and the crew members watching the camp at night never saw anyone come or go. As the days progressed, more and more of the survivors went missing and the captain began to take more security measures to prevent anyone disappearing, yet the crew we growing ever more paranoid and began turning on each other out of fear that one of their own was doing the others harm. More days passed and now with all of his crew disappeared without a trace, the captain was now alone on the island and desperately trying not to sleep for fear that he too would disappear in the morning, when he spotted a ship on the horizon, but he could not call out to it as the tiredness drew him into slumber. The next morning, a rescue ship arrived on the island after noticing the lifeboats ashore, but found no trace of the survivors; so the rescuers decided to spend a night on the island to look further, but the next morning found one of their crew was missing.

Shaun slowly opened his eyes. It was blurry at first but after his vision became clear he realised he was under a canopy of leaves as far as the eye could see. "What happened how did I get here?" he thought to himself. He slowly picked himself off the ground, wiping the soil off himself. He started to walk, unsure which way was the right way. "Hello" he shouted out Nothing. "HELLO" louder he shouted but all he could hear was the sound of his heart beating fast in his chest.

Landing on the planet Huypto began during the sunset which is more beautiful than can ever be imagined. This place can only be described as a jungle of colour, it is a place you would see in the films made purely from animation. Life on Huypto is more peaceful and relaxing to that on earth with creatures that are not fixated on pray. Food is existing naturally with vibrant fruits similar to dragonfruit. Being a carnivore here seems a concept that would have never existed. I begin my first few hours on Huypto by exploring the surroundings and picking somewhere that myself and my colleagues will make as our base. It is seeming to be more of a holiday than an exploration job so far. My view from my tipi is like a picture, I never want to leave this place!

David and Allesandra joined the crew of The Falcon - a small but hardy boat - in the morning.  They were excited to explore the new world and unravel the riches entombed within the depths.  As they embarked on their journey with the experienced crew, they quickly found themselves in a scary environment or incredible storms, fighting, and dangerous winds.  Many treasures were found - hidden jewels and coins were their favourite.  But after a time they found themselves uninspired - truly their real passion was spending time together.  They spent some time selling all their treasure along the coast of the old world, while talking about their great adventures to the public.  Eventually they found a beautiful cove with an old farm building.  They remodelled it and spent the rest of their life happy there, together.

Two childhood best friends embark on an adventure through the woods. Little did they know that soon after they will fall into a tragedy. Carelessly thinking of having a fun time exploring they ignored the big sign at the entrance of the jungle saying "ENTER AT YOUR OWN RISK." The two best friends did not know that there would not be able to turn back, they will be forever trapped. After a few long hours they decided their fun was over and wanted to return home, not realising that the entrance is no longer there, as if they entered into a labyrinth. Frantically running around in hopes to escape the wicked place of a jungle. Little did they know the more they run the more trapped they are. Days have gone by and they started to slowly transition into the forest until the two best friends were nothing left but the trees themselves.

After travelling for 14 earth years, the crew has finally landed on a planet that was thought to have resources that doesn't exist on any other planet. The crew was tasked to get a sample of the material and analyse it in their lab. The planet reported was to be a planet that had nothing of human value, presumably an empty space full of rocks. As the space shuttle doors opened, the crew were at awe. The planet looked exactly like planet earth, just never touched by a human. The crew proceeded to step on the planet and to their surprise, the planet had living organisms. Grass, flowers, tress were growing. This could a revolutionary step towards human evolution; - said a crew member.

Three young teenagers and their robot companion embark on a thrilling journey to find out the history of where they came from. They need to travel to a distant planet, which is filled with breath-taking landscapes and unparalleled biodiversity, unlike anything they have seen before. After they land on the planet, they disembark from the ship and start to navigate the terrain. It was a dangerous journey but they start to learn about the ancient civilizations that once built the planet. They find out these alien species was very similar to themselves, same type of form as them, and similar artefacts that they use.  Whilst everything was different, everything they saw reminded them of home. They knew this was the right planet. They continues their expedition to find out the answers they went searching for.

Three friends embark on an exhilarating journey through an uncharted jungle, discovering hidden ancient ruins filled with treasures. Upon touching the treasure the ruins started to rumble and quake as the ground lurched below them. The three friends sprang into action in an effort to avoid the trap, they ran full speed vaulting over crumbled rocks and sliding through narrow gaps barely escaping the ruins as the walls caved in. As they continued along the way, they encountered various wild animals but none more horrifying than the pack of lions. The lions gave chase to the three friends and they ran for dear life leading to a rickety rope bridge. As they neared the end of the rope bridge a sickening snapping sound filled the air as the rope bridge gave way under the weight of the lions and the friends. Diving towards the end the friends managed to grasp some of the remaining planks of the rope bridge and climb the remaining few feet to safety. Upon returning home, the friends regaled the village people on their adventures and were celebrated as heroes.

Alice woke up from the pain in her legs. Her last memory was the warning lights flashing on the plane journey to Thailand. In disbelief, she looked around to see only dense trees and jungle. She managed to hobble up despite the a throbbing pain in her legs. In the distance she could see parts of the airplane amongst smoke and debris. She stood back trying to comprehend the situation, she was lost in the jungle without anyone else around. She walked through the trees and looked up at the trees to see the native birds flying between branches. "Help" she screamed at the top of her voice in despair.

While searching for a hidden ancient treasure in the depths of the jungle, a group of brave explores encounters challenging obstacles and dangerous creatures.  Through teamwork and determination, they manage to overcome these perils.  This leads to them uncovering the lost city they were seeking.   In the end they learn that the true treasure lies not in the material riches they discover.  The real treasure was the memories and friendships forged during their amazing adventure.  They went on to form strong friendships that spanned a lifetime.  They grew together, they grew old together.  They left this world together.

A ragtag group of intergalactic explorers are sent to explore a mysterious new planet. Traversing treacherous terrain the group finally come across the planets secrets in all their glory. An adventure none of this group were ever ready for, a mission that will stretch them to their limits. Hidden amongst the mountains is a secret base, filled with strange beings. Are they friendly? Are they dangerous? Creeping into the base they are shocked to see the beings standing round monitors commanding their forces against earth. What will our heroes do, what can they do, is this the end?

Traveling on the rough and storm seas, petal grew concerned of how they where going to survive the ever raging storm ahead. The wind swept across the swishing waters splashing petal in the face with the fresh sea breeze. The ever darkening storm cloud bellowed above with the sound of the whistling wind. The boat was swaying from side to side as the waves crashed along side the boat traveling at some speed to get away from the following storm behind. The seas start to calm and the waves start to relax and petal catches her breathe. Finally they have sailed through the storm and everything seems to be calm. As petal sails by on her boat across the seas she passed all sorts of magically beings such as dolphins jumping through there air glistening as the sun kisses there skin. The turtles swim close to the boat looking up and petal and almost smile above the water and them zoom off back to the depths of the sea.

Ollie, Alfie and Joseph has been planning their Jungle get away for a long time and when they arrived they were not disappointed. It was just like in the movies, dangerous, exciting, thrilling and awesome!! They saw many creatures on their travels, some they had only ever read about it books and some no one would ever believe existed if they told them. Some of the creatures they met helped them along the way and guided them through safe passages. They didn't realise the resilience and strength they would need for this adventure until they were there or how much their friendship would mean to them when times got tough. By being somewhere so untouched by man, they realised the struggles of the western world and how more isn't necessarily better. They wanted to use their experience to try and make the world a better place.

The ground was soft and squishy. It felt like walking on mashmallows. I couldn't see ahead as I was surrounded by foliage. It was so quiet. I ducked under branches and the leaves rustled around me. The only sound. I spied a clearing. Was anybody there?

Stephen, the Captain, completed his pre-flight checks and after a brief pause commenced his take off.
