Looking ahead he could see the relative motion of the spaceship as his surroundings the launch pad superstructure, the control point buildings and the direct communication bridges and the seemed to be going backwards past him.  The vibrations of the space craft as it set out on its inter-stella voyage seemed somehow soothing, but Stephen wondered how long it would be before they became annoying.  He glanced at the pursers display - showing the stocks carried for the long journey ahead and wondered at the range of items he new was included for use on voyages such as this.  Suddenly a loud series of alerts alarms sounded, lots of lights and the vessel began to shake violently, the helper computers display flickered and then steadied - showing the death sentence of all space vehicles - fatal fuel leak, commence abandon ship procedures.  Stephen hit the eject button to shoot the self powered people pod away from the now doomed spaceship - the failure having taken place too soon after takeoff for any other such manoeuvring - and saw with satisfaction the display telling him the pod was away on its controlled landing.  Hitting the control to use the remaining power to guide the wreck to crash onto a safe landing spot, and commenced the final abandonment of the now barely in control ship Stephen sat back to wait.  Well done said a voice in his ear - you passed the simulator again - as Stephen smiled to himself and hoped it would never happen for real.

It was late December when a group of fearless explorers decided to set sail on the open seas in search of the legendary lost treasure of the pirate king named Silver Sword. They had found a treasure map whilst searching a cave that was reputed to be the final resting place of the legendary pirate which showed the location of Silver Swords treasure on a remote undiscovered island across the sea. Once they set sail they encountered many challenges that almost led to them giving up including a fierce storm, which nearly sank the ship, and also an encounter with a huge sea creature a massive octopus which dragged a few of the group into the ocean where they drowned. They continued to travel across the sea and overcame the storms and sea creature through team work, managing to navigate the rough seas, storms and escaping the beast until they reached their final destination. Though perseverance the remaining group reached the mysterious island and made their way towards the location of the treasure marked on the map, excited to uncover the treasure that had been lost for centuries and which would make the losses and difficulties encountered worthwhile. They made their way across the island when they found a massive structure which looked like a castle with a door with symbols on it, the symbols were mentioned on the back of the map and explorers found that they had to move these symbols in a certain pattern to open the door which they did. The door opened and there was a massive room and in the center was gold as far as the eye could see and diamond, rubies and emeralds, the explorer were filled with joy and happiness that they had reached their goal and discovered the treasure. One of the explorers picked up a piece of gold which immediately triggered a trap- the door closed behind them and out came a giant dragon, they knew that there was no escape and that this would be their final resting place, despite their best efforts to fight back the dragon killed them all and the legendary treasure remains hidden to this day- a warning to those that greed can lead to death.

In our adventure to another planet we left Earth with great intrepidation. Never before had anyone from Earth embarked on such an adventure. The journey will take around 4 1/2 years and in that time me and the rest of the crew shall spend alot of time together. I have always been fascinated by space travel and I cannot believe the day has come when I will experince this. On arriving at the planet we slowly tocuh down on the surface of the planet. As the door opens we wonder what we will face. My heart is racing as the door opens. There in front of us is an alien!

We landed on the gloomy orange planet and immediately felt a blast of warm air. This place was much more humid and hot than back home. We wandered over the mounds, looking around the barren, empty space. As we peered over a larger mound, we found a large lake of green liquid bubbling at the surface. Suddenly there was a loud quake in the Earth and large creatures emerged from the crack and from the glowing lake. We stood in shock until one creature let out a large shriek, showing a huge sharp set of teeth and a blood-stained smile, and hurtled towards us on all fours. We bolted back to the ship, diving inside it and quickly taking off as the creatures clawed at the door. We breathe a sigh of relief as we ascend; until we look down and see one of our team still down there; the creatures ripping into him, but it was too late!

We travelled to mars. James jumped off the spaceship and onto the surface. A lot of dust covered the visor of his helmet. Once he had wiped the dust off, he saw mars in all its glory. There were a lot of mountainous areas surrounding us. I jumped off after James. I could feel a rocky texture to the ground beneath me. We started walking to the martian base nearby.

Sumi had been part of the crew for almost 6 weeks now. She had never been on a boat before, but found herself adapting to the pirate life better than expected. That being said, the pirate life had been less than she had expected, with nothing but sailing and scrubbing. The only highlight of her day was scran and she could already smell whatever the cooks were dishing up today, which was leaving her in a world of her own wondering what it could be.    "Snap out of it Sumi" came an abrupt shout from the familiar voice of her newest friend, Jonesy.    Sumi looked up at where Jonesy's voice had come from and followed his extended finger the the horizon, off of the ship's starboard side.    It took a couple of seconds before Sumi spotted the object in the distance, but when she did, an emotion that was a strange concoction of fear and excitement took over her. Finally, she was about to experience the real life of a pirate.

A group of about 50 students from a college went on an adventurous open sea trip. They planned to go surfing in the ocean. Most of the students started to surf and some of them went a bit deeper in to the ocean and suddenly one of the student saw a shark and shouted. Everybody was terrified and started to surf back to the shore. But there were a few students who slipped and fell into the ocean. They were terrified to the core that they didn't know what to do. One of the students who fell into the water began to sink and was helped by others to safety. At last it was known that there was no shark in the water and it was a prank by one of the student.

I suppose I should start with the plane crash. One minute I was asleep in the air, the next thing I knew I was awake in the wreckage of the plane, staring at what could only be described as dense jungle. The other passengers had disappeared and I was alone in the densely humid greenery, surrounded by sounds I neither knew nor understood. Screwing up my courage, I unbuckled my safety belt and tentatively ventured out. I had only taken a few steps when I heard a rustling behind me and turned to see a pair of baleful amber eyes staring at me. The creature behind the eyes turned out to be a stunningly beautiful tiger. Before I had chance to react, the tiger was on top of me bearing its teeth. In the next instance I heard the voices of my friends laughing and calling out "Eaten by a tiger in the first five minutes - your game play sucks, man!"

The group of friends blearily opened their eyes, adjusting to the dim light as they adjusted to their new surroundings. It quickly became clear that their plane had crashed as they tended to their cuts and scrapes - it looked like they were the only survivors! Louisa quickly suggested that they split up into 4 groups and head in separate directions in the hope of finding civilisation and rescue. Strange noises coming from the jungle made each of the friends nervous; they gathered up sharp sticks, rocks and other items to use as weapons to defend themselves. Despite their anxiety, there was also an air of excitement, they were excited to explore the jungle and the ruins found within. Jack and Kate headed out first, soon stumbling across what looked like an abandoned temple. Heading slowly deeper into the ruins, they stumbled across a box full of notes and maps. The notes seemed nonsensical but also urged the reader not to stay in the temple but to escape to the north as quickly as possible where there was apparently a small village.

The "open seas" always struck me as an odd phrase, but I was beginning to understand where it came from. I don't think there is anything more endless, open and mesmerising than the view from a boat as it noses through the waves. No phone signal, no comforts, but a feeling of being ultimately alive and in contact with nature. The sun feels stronger than ever, and I'm beginning to think of the heat as my companion on this voyage. A bold, confident companion who, with a bit of luck, knows where we are going. It all feels like an adventure, even though I booked this trip months ago. Each island looks like heaven, each port like it's been populated down the ages with people living sun-filled, happy lives with space and time to look out at the sea. My adventure is just beginning.

Deep in the dense jungle amongst tall trees and a multitude of wildlife a group of young explorers embarked on a daring adventure. Their quest was to find a legendary crystal said to hold magical powers. Along their journey they encountered many challenging obstacles that blocked their path. They were following an ancient    map given to them by an old man in their village. He said they must be careful as great danger is never far from the crystal. They eventually found the crystal and were relieved to be unhurt in their quest for it. They returned the crystal to a museum when they got home and felt a great sense of pride. The crystal remains on display in the museum to this day.

Not your typical holiday, but my adventure into the jungle was incredible! I always thought these adventures were very dangerous, but it was actually really fun. I have seen an amazing bout of nature that I never would have seen otherwise. If you are used to living in the monotonous life of the city, where the only influences of nature are the parks, then it will blow you away. I tried completely new foods. I had seen animals I'd never seen before. I even learned this unheard-of language. I highly recommend it.

Some years ago there was a man named Rob who enjoyed exploring many different places. He had a particular fascination with animals in the jungle and decided that he wanted to go and explore one. His parents however were not keen as they considered it too dangerous. He didn't care about this and one night left his home on his own and travelled to the jungle on foot. There he saw many wondrous things including moneys, birds and also a gorilla. The gorilla initially scared him but after a while he went close to the gorilla and to his surprise it spoke to him in pure English. "My name is Jeff" said the gorilla, "what is your name?".

The breeze blew her hair wildly, and the smell of the ocean filled her senses. Looking across the blue, shining water , she was overwhelmed by the beauty surrounding her. Would she ever return to the home she knew, or was that life forever lost? How could the world have such cruelty, it made no sense. Maybe she would be rescued when they returned to land, a miracle of kindness to salve her pain. Hearing a voice, she turned around. The face looking at her was familiar, a face she had longed to see once more. There is no bond stronger than that of a mother to their child.

The Island, shrouded in mist lay just beyond the rocks.  Getting there, meant navigating a treacherous course across open seas, swirling in the pounding rain.      Jack, turned to his men and nodded!  "Set sail to the Island, take care, we need to get there in one piece!    Ahead of them lay an unchartered territory with the potential for many riches.  But first they needed to claim ownership of the land.    Behind them, the shadows of another fleet, gained territory minute by minute.    It was a race to the finish.

Today was the day that we set off to explore Mars, the first humans to have ever set foot on the planet. There was a mixture of excitement and fear in the air and I felt butterflies dancing around in my stomach as I stepped in to the rocket. A million thoughts were racing around my mind; the journey, whether we would be safe, who would be watching from Earth and what astronaut food tastes like but one question in particular would not escape my thoughts. What if we weren't alone when we arrived? What if there really is life on another planet? The idea that I might meet an alien today was both terrifying and amazing. What would I ask an alien? What would YOU ask an alien?

A group of young friends embark on a thrilling open sea adventure, searching for a fabled lost island. Their journey started at Dover. Its filled with challenges from monstrous sea creatures to pirates. When they finally discover a lost island, they work together to unlock its secrets and claim its riches. Riches left by unknow past visitors. Their adventure tests their friendships to the limit. Its a story of courage and love. How will it end ?

Setting sail in a pirate vessel. Across the Indian ocean. What a beautiful sight. Steering the ship amid the hot temperatures. Admiring the wonderful clear sea. The sea is calm. We anchor just off the coast. And dive in the deep blue sea.

A crew of rag-tag sailors have set out on a dangerous journey across the open seas in search of the fabled treasure of Azarath. The captain came into the possession of a map leading to a supposedly empty area in the middle of the ocean, that indicates the treasure is buried there. As they approach the location they see that in fact there is no land but there is an enormous turtle, 500 times larger than normal. They board the turtles shell and continue to the centre. In the centre they find a person standing motionless. They approach and the person holds out a hand with a glowing gem in their palm. In silence, the captain takes the gem and all around him reality appears to warp and bend. He rouses himself and finds that he is on shore with his crew, map in hand planning to head out to the treasure of Azarath, however, he and his crew have no recollection that they have taken this journey over 5,000 times already.

The six looked out at the horizon as it seemed to be full circles of many rainbows moving around them.  Not a sound could be heard except the panicked breathing of six extremely scared children who felt like life had taken their world from them.  It had.  The ground they stood on was a totally alien substance.  The air they breathed felt fresh, almost tasty, and cold.  As their hearts started to beat faster and faster, the shape in the rainbow appeared to move closer to the little group.  Their eyes started to dart from the rainbow, to the strange shape, advancing without moving, to  each other.  There was nowhere to run.

The young lads embarked on a adventure onboard their boat. They came across a storm soon after. They stayed afloat with luck on their side. The day after they saw an uninhabitated island where they landed. They explored this mysterious island of beauty. They will remember this adventure in to their old age and reminice.  The experience will prepare for more adventures in their lives. This will be a good start to more adventures to follow.

The three teens had been on an adventure course the previous week and to this end had found themselves embarking on a voyage in a small dinghy from a private jetty belonging to the father of one of them (Raffie). It was after midnight and the moon lit them up as they pushed off excitedly. Shap, who was the natural leader  looked at his compass confidently and steered north west, not noticing something brushing his oar lightly. After 20 minutes or so, a fin appeared alongside them, dipping occasionally. Noticing it, Lara, the youngest, clutched at her brother Finn, nearly knocking him out of the boat in fright. The panic was contagious as everyone started standing up and knocking into each other, pointing and shouting. Raffie and Shap quickly turned the boat and began to head for shore but the fin turned with them and followed ominously. Picking up the pace, the boys paddled furiously and made for shore as fast as they could.

Whilst taking a spaceship to venture into an unknown orbit we had to make an emergency landing. This planet was bright and cheery and hopefully there would be life. We walked through lovely forests with trees so big you couldnât imagine. It was quite eerie though, far too silent. Yet there must be some sort of life. We kept walking and stumbled across a beautiful waterfall. But this waterfall was something I had never seen   Before. Colors you wouldnât imagine. This is where a journey begins

Ok, I'm not exactly Bear Grylls or whatever his name is - how the heck am I supposed to survive out here? Is it because his name is 'Bear' that he gets to thrive in these sh***y conditions? Maybe I should think of myself as a 'Forrest' to psychologically up my game... Forrest: that is my new name, now, and I'm ready to face anything. Wait, wasn't he ret- intellectually challenged in that movie? Plan B: I'm River.

Deep in the heart of the dense jungle, a group of adventurous friends embarked on a thrilling expedition. Their eyes widened as they stepped onto the untrodden path, surrounded by towering emerald trees. The symphony of exotic birdcalls echoed through the air, enchanting their senses. They followed the winding trail, their hearts pounding with anticipation. As they ventured deeper, the dense foliage seemed to whisper ancient secrets, awakening their curiosity. Suddenly, they stumbled upon a hidden waterfall, its cascading waters shimmering in the dappled sunlight. They marveled at it's beauty, feeling the refreshing mist on their faces. With newfound energy, they continued their journey, eager to uncover the jungles mysteries and create memories that would last a lifetime.

Three friends embark on a thrilling adventure to a distant, unfamiliar plane. Amidst alien landscapes and unknown dangers, they unlock an ancient secret, revealing the planet's hidden connection to Earth's history. The secret involves the discovery of a completely new species, not dissimilar to the human species. Their newfound knowledge ultimately transforms life on both worlds, forever cementing their bond across galaxies. All three friends go through their own journey as they explore and discover this new unfamiliar planet. At times, this causes friction between them but their friendship is strong and survive a lot. They face dangers and uncertainties, but their sense of adventure pulls them through. They have interesting times ahead of them!

Many years into the future, a new planet was discovered. The planet was very far away, and not many people knew of its existence. When the first colonists started to arrive there, it was still very wild and dangerous. Despite the danger, many people were drawn to there in pursuit of wealth and adventure. Many others were trying to escape into the unknown wilderness. The rapid advancement of technology had improved many aspects of society on paper, but left some people disillusioned with their lives. These people wanted to return to a more primitive and meaningful way of life. The newly discovered remote planet provided many with the opportunity.

Oh my god, I need to tell you about my trip.   So, my mom said I could have the day off school to go anywhere I liked.   Of course I picked the amazing planet of The Brink! I was so excited, I couldn't wait to try their upside down drinks and multi flavour cakes.   I had a brilliant but weird day, I can't wait to show you the photos!   The air was different and the water was pink, what can I say, it was up there with one of the best days of my life!   I will have to take you to meet the eccentric people that live there.   We will go together one day.

The commander is the first to exit the ship, as a prideful man, he is always the first to put himself in danger. His 2 colleagues follow him hesitantly, this is the first planet they've encountered that other alien life has been  present. They see fields of a soft teal, the texture all wrong to be grass, and what they think to be trees off into the distance, bundled together like a dense forest.   "It's not every day you get to see a view like that." One of the crewmates stated, eyes grazing over to the distance in awe. She ran her hands through the teal fields of the mysterious plant life, pollen picking up to the grips of her fingerprints.   They walked until they met the forests entrance, where the commander made sure his crew expected to be ready for anything. Before they could continue their venture, a rythmic heart-beat sound was heard, distant but loud enough to vibrate the ground they stood on.

The forest was so dense, the vegetation making it impossible to see more than a few feet in front of you. Apart from the sounds of my feet on the jungle floor rustling leaves and snapping twigs it was eerily quiet. I am not alone, I can feel something or someone looking at me, the hairs on the back of my neck tingle sending a shiver down my spine. A shrill shriek makes me jump, all of a sudden the jungle is full of noise, a deafening roar surrounds me. I panic and break into a run, tripping over the undergrowth, crashing to the ground. Head spinning, I open my eyes, crouched in front of me is a Tiger, eyes gleaming, mouth opening. Panic sets in, there is no escape, this magnificent beast is poised and ready to pounce. I hear a scream, briefly wondering where the noise is coming from before I realise that it is me.

They tightened up their seat belts as the spaceship dodged the incoming rain of falling objects. Why is it that the rain of stones is at it's season again. It will be like this for the next four weeks. The roofs of the houses will be filled with holes and dents again. But Wade is happy his underground refuge is already finished. That's where they're going right now. He is with his family and friends. His pet dog is with him also.

The wind howled like a pack of wolves. Waves the height of Big Ben tossed the little sail boat all over the place. A rope snapped and spiraled over the sailor's head. Quickly the small man tightened his lifeline to the mast and lunged at the whipping rope. He grabbed the other discarded half and pulled the two parts together. The tighter half needed to be kept in place, so the sailor jammed his foot down to pin the line and stop it moving. A wave crash over the side and drenched the entire boat. With numbing cold hands, the sailor managed to knot the two halves together and allow the tension to keep the knot in place.

When a group of unlikely strangers form a bond on a daring voyage across the open seas, they battle treacherous weather and fearsome pirates in search of a legendary treasure. As they navigate uncharted waters and face their greatest fears, they forge lifelong friendships and discover the true meaning of adventure. In the end, they learn that life's greatest riches are the unexpected bonds and experiences shared on the journey, rather than the destination itself.     They were taken far out to sea, with only each other to look after. They saw many sites as they approached sore, in the distance was a huge castle with a spike on the top of it which you could see for miles.   They headed over there to see if any treasure was lying around but came across some grumpy guards that would not let them any further into the grounds. They ended up turning back to their ship and sailing away disheartened. It was only on the return journey that they realised if they hadn't have had each other then the journey would have felt much worse.

A long time ago, a pirate ship became marooned on a mysterious island due to a freak tropical storm. After several weeks of the crew surviving on scavenged supplies, the captain proposed they should explore the dark mysterious jungle that covered most of the inner island. On their fourth night of exploring, just as they were about to head back in despair, a strange, cloaked figure appeared at their camp. "Leave this place" it hissed, in a strange, inhuman tone. After a moment of being frozen in fear, the group scampered. As they ran back through the forest, it seemed to become alive, with strange whooping and crashing, as if the entire jungle was chasing them. Once they reached the coast, the ship was, to their astonishment, afloat, with the rest of the crew beckoning them to make haste and climb aboard. As they sailed to safety, the mysterious island behind them seemed to fade into mist, and finally to nothing.

After 16 long days at sea, the crew of young sailors were growing tired and bored of seeing nothing but ocean, and their desire to discover new land and uncover the treasure it may hold was growing thin . Suddenly, a loud yell from the top deck shocked everyone awake from their afternoon daze. "Land! Land!", yelled Matthew running along the deck to grab the ship wheel and steer it in the direction of the unrecognised island in the near distance. The whole crew jumped and ran to the edge of the ship to catch a glimpse of the island before them. The water splashed beneath them as they ogled the small island covered in jungle and tall mountains. The crew was mesmerised by an almost glittery coat that covered the land, and the ship sailed quickly towards the shore, almost as if it was been guided by an unknown force.

In the distant galaxy of Xeloria, amidst the shimmering nebulae and celestial wonders, lay a mysterious planet called zephyria. A brave explorer, was chosen for a daring mission to uncover the planets secrets. Equipped with high-tech space suits she then descended on to the alien terrain. She then encountered a fae-like inhabitants. They guided her to an ancient temple. She was amazed at what they had developed and what they have created.   She then embarked on a quest to find out what else lived on this planet.   With courage she decided to dedicate all her time to accomplish this mission.

We crashed. We crashed in the jungle. The plane was split in two, half of the passengers were dead, the other half were either really shaken up or walking wounded. It was raining but super humid. My guess was that we were in a rain forest in some part of Brazil. We walked in the direction of what we thought was North to see where it would take us, we figured that if we followed a straight line, it must lead us too somewhere eventually. We had no food but we had some water, we needed to find some food if we were to survive. We foraged for berries and fruit, not knowing what was safe to eat so eating little at a time to see if it was safe.

The explorer and his party of fellow explorers and local people to do the carrying of equipment and supplies were finally ready to set off on their journey to find the lost tribe. It was to be a journey into the unknown, to a largely unexplored part of the jungle. Many potential hazards are likely to be ahead of them, tricky terrain, and dangerous animals just two of the potential dangers. They would be taking enough food to last up to two weeks and maps, such that was available. They planned to do at least 6 hours walking each day, so all the party were required to be fit and healthy. The first day was going well they were making progress quicker than expected. After about 6 hours they found themselves in a bit of a clearing, so decided to make camp for the night. However, they found they had forgotten to pack tents so they would have to return to base and start again later!

As the wind started to blow north east I dropped the sail down as far it would go, the wind caught the sail to perfection, the boat turned gently north east, splashing the water, our adventure had begun.    The wind increased and with that so did the speed of the boat, with the sun beaming down and in my eyes it was a struggle to see the horizon, but i could smell that sea air, the unmistakeable smell of salt, freshness and seaweed.    We were now going at a good speeding, dashing through the water like a hot knife through butter, i wont deny that i wasnt scared, this was all knew to me but the excitement of the voyage and what I was about to see outweighed the fear.    With our destination reached a few miles from shore we raised the sail to reduce speed and come to a stop, dropping anchor this was the place we wanted to be.    I feared we would have to wait a while bobbing on the ocean to see my favourite animal, the great white shark, but almost in a way that seemed scripted the sharks dorsal fin broke the waters surface.    Gliding slowly yet purposefully around our boat the shark was almost investigating us to see what we were doing in its domain .    Seeing the full size it must have been 20feet in length, a real big one but as quickly as he arrived the shark then vanished to the depths of the ocean bed.    My dream had come true and like that it was over, we lowered the sail and set back to shore, it was the best day of my life.

I felt the leaves of the African jungle brush past my arm as a pushed through them.  the feeling of my feet into the ground inch by inch after each step. But I cannot give up, I am not leaving this Jungle without the president. I heard a scream coming from one of the trees. I rushed to see what it was. With pure shock in my eyes I see the president getting eating by the biggest snake I have ever seen. I cannot do anything but watch. He was a larger man and the snake was only able to eat half of him.

Author had not seen his old friends since finishing astronaut training almost seven years ago, he was delighted when they all said they would come for a belated Birthday weekend to visit the newly built casino city of sin province on Mars. Usually Author will partake in a few shots of Martian liquor when he is frying the space ship with no consequences. Unfortunately he is usually flying alone with no distractions. On this occasion there was plenty of distractions. In the celebrations of Authors belated Birthday and his 4 oldest friends and the Martian liquor flowing a catastrophe was looming. Author saw the lights below of the city of sin and lowered the ship not realizing exactly how close those lights really were until he smashed through the front of the newly built Martian Palace Casino. The glass front was completely collapsed, Author and his friends were unhurt physically but there was much damaged pride, the Martian security however were so angry they were foaming at the mouth. Author and his friends spent the belated Birthday weekend in a Martian cold cell nursing a hangover, they all agreed next year to just send a card.

When the team landed on this distant and harsh environment, they were initially apprehensive, but also filled with a sense of exhilaration. It took a while to conjure up the nerves to take a step out of their space capsule, but knowing that they had a job to do and had planned and rehearsed this moment so many times they took the plunge.     They were armed with cameras, scientific tools, sample bags and other equipment needed for their mission. But they got interrupted when a large creature appeared in front of them. It did not appear to be friendly and started to walk towards them. Fear and panic gripped them, so they decided to move away slowly. The creature followed at a distance, but they continued exploring this amazing landscape and wondering into caves and finding themselves faced with strange and incredible things. They were making good headway with their analyses and photography, but decided to make a hasty retreat back to their capsule when additional creatures started appearing on the horizon and decided to come back at a later time.

Bob and Michelle were on a paddleboarding date, and had been exploring the islands off the coast, from where they both lived.     As they took a rest on their boards and sat chatting, hours passed, time flew by and before they knew it the sun was setting and they'd floated out to sea.     Looking around them, no islands or land was in sight.     They both began to panic.    Seeing a small fishing boat on the horizon, they knew that their only chance of rescue was to reach it.     Exhausted, they both paddled furiously for what felt like hours.    When they eventually reached the fishing boat the shocked fisherman pulled them aboard.    Bob and Michelle were rescued, and after a long habilitation process, they went on to live a long and happy life together.

Our school trip to Cape Town ended in a disaster when our plane crashed into the deep Congo jungle.  There were twenty five of us students and three teachers, we were all pretty close and got on well.  It was a huge shock for us to crash land and we all kept thinking about Lord of the Flies and making silly jokes in our shocked state of minds.  Luckily, everyone survived and our teachers took charge and managed to calm us down.  The first thing we did was build shelters, as the jungle nights were going to be really scary, with all those creatures prowling around.  The main shelter we built was near to a beautiful, deep blue lagoon.   It was wonderful to wake in the morning and swim in the lagoon and feel the sunlight on our faces.  After the shock of the crash, after a couple of weeks we all began to feel more relaxed, we had a good routine of looking for food and cooking it around a campfire each evening.

Some curious astronauts wanting to explore the beauty of the universe travelled to space. They were shocked to discover weird animals in the first planet they visited. When they got the second planet they found debris of a spaceship belonging to Russia. Amidst their adventure, they got to the next planet where the weather was not favorable.  At the third planet, they discovered there were strange elements. They took samples to test the importance of this element.  When they got to the third and last planet they were discouraged that they did not find life on that planet.  They spent few days on that planet, after three days, they returned back to earth.

After unexpectedly uncovering a centuries old treasure map, a daring group of friends embark on a thrilling voyage across the treacherous open seas. Aya, Nox, Sasha and Anna have been best friends since before they could remember. Desperate to rid themselves of poverty, they steal a glorious sailboat from the Mayor's entitled son. Struggling against tumultuous waters, storms, and a persistent mythical sea creature, they push the limits of their courage and resolve in the pursuit of an ancient mystery. Racing across the ocean, they hope to achieve which countless others died attempting. Things become complicated when a gang of pirates suddenly appear, demanding ownership of the treasure map and threatening to take it by force. When eighteen year old Aya realises she is falling in love with the leader of the pirates, Zion, she is forced to make a tough decision. As long-lost secrets are uncovered, bonds are tested and the crew discovers that the true treasure lies in the camaraderie and friendships forged on the open seas.

As the smoke billowed from the plane and its contents strewn across the jungle floor, I found myself unscathed apart from a few scratches and blood streaming from my throbbing head.   I check to see if the other occupants of the plane are alive but the pilot is dead and so is the other couple that was on board the private plane with their bodies mangled up in the debris.    I sit in shock at what had just happened, how is anyone going to know where our plane has crashed in the middle of the jungle and how am I going to get help. I dare not venture into the heart of the perilous jungle and treacherous terrain. From above I could see for miles and I am in the middle of a deep uninhabited jungle that stretches for miles and I gather my strength and go through the debris looking for food, water and anything useful that I could use to call for help. I hear the wildlife of the jungle and see to the left of me in the distance there is a clearing and ledge that I could possibly climb to see a better view of my location. I start to make my way through the deep and heavy jungle vines to the clearing ahead. The shock is starting the wear off and in turn the numbness of the pain is subsiding to and now I find myself in agony and bleeding quite heavy as I climb the rocks which seem like eternity and on the ledge I see something in the distance.

In the heart of a dense jungle, a group of young adventures embarked on an exhilarating quest.   Armed with a map shrouded in mystery, they ventured into an ancient temple.  This became the gateway to a realm where reality intertwined with fantasy.   The temple tested their intellect and agility through perilous challenges, unveiling a long-hidden secret of great significance.   Their unwavering teamwork and determination allowed them to decipher intricate puzzles, leading them to discover a potent artefact.   Recognising its immense power, they made a solemn pledge to protect it from those who sought to exploit it.   As they emerged from the depths of the temple, they were forever changed by their experience.   Their incredible journey became a tale whispered amongst the masses, igniting the spark of adventure in the hearts of countless dreamers.

The sky on Planet Xelios burned with hues of crimson as Kira, a young explorer from Earth, stepped onto alien soil. Equipped with her trusty bio-suit, she ventured forth into a forest pulsating with bio luminescent flora. Glowing tendrils brushed against her as she walked carefully, drawn bu an otherworldly melody. Following the ethereal sounds, she stumbled upon a hidden civilisation, inhabited by beings of pure energy. Their leader, Lumina, offered Kira a glimpse into their collective consciousness, revealing forgotten histories and boundless wisdom. As darkness threatened to engulf their world, Kira discovered an ancient artifact - the Prism of Light. Harnessing its power, she ignited the dormant star, revitalising the planet. In gratiude, the energy beings gifted her a crystalline pendant, forever linking her to their realm. With her mission complete, Kira bid farewell, promising to return and share the wonders of Xelios with her fellow Earthlings, forever changed by her intergalactic odyssey

When Jim, Alison and Charles woke up, things were very different.  The night before there had been an intense electrical storm which coincided with the summer solstice AND a solar eclipse.  Somehow this had caused a tear in the space time continuum that occurred exactly in their house and they had been transported to a different planet.  The first thing that became apparent was the sweet, almost sickly smell in the atmosphere, which they could breathe easily without apparatus.  The second thing they noticed, were the strange, unearthly plants and vegetation the grew all around them which they suspected, was the cause of the sickly sweet smell.  They decided to explore to see if they could find something, anything to help them and found a weird creature which seemed to be some kind of animal crossed with some kind of fungus.  After much deliberation they decided to eat some of the fungus, Charles offered to go first and promptly disappeared.  What happened next we will never know, as Jim and Alison met the same fate.

once upon a time, two friends set out for a thrilling adventure in a jungle. there they found a lost ancient temple. Inside the temple was lost treasure that possess supernatural powers. the friends must learn new trick and pass all puzzles to be able to access the treasure and take it home. one of the friend was calm and start learning the language with which the temple instructions were written. The other was going around checkng if there was a back door to the treasure. luckily the friend learned the language and passed all puzzles. they finally got the treasure and went home happy.

Once upon a time there was a brave young girl. One day, she decided it was time for an adventure. She gathered a group of friends and embarked deep into the heart of the jungle, on a thrilling journey to find a lost city rumoured to hold ancient treasures. Together they encountered venomous snakes, deceptive quicksand, and hostile native tribes. Relying on each other for support, they were courageous and determined, and eventually came upon the legendary lost city. As they explored the city, they came to realise the true treasure was their journey of self-discovery and the friendships they built along the way. Of course, they also located the ACTUAL treasure and decided to split it amongst themselves equally. They each took their share home and lived happily ever after.

One sunny day, whilst on an expedition to the thick green jungle to study rare and unusual plants, a varied team of daring young scientists stumbled along. Eventually, an old and eccentric local guide helped the team to navigate the treacherous terrain to uncover a lost cities ancient secrets. Together, they navigated the treacherous terrain and faced many unexpected and dangerous challenges in order to reach their goal.  They discovered the true meaning of friendship, bravery and comradeship on their challenging journey.  At last they reached the ancient lost city and it rose up above them as they sheltered in it's haunting shadow.  Slowly and carefully the scientists navigated their way through the lost city taking in the sights and sounds.  Never before in their lives had any of them seen such amazing sight. When all of a sudden there was the most terrifying roar that shook the ground.

As the man ventured deeper into the woods, he began to lose track of his whereabout. The jungle grew thicker and thicker with each step as he lost his bearing completely. In a panic, he started to run as best he could towards the sound of flowing water. Little did he know, he was heading for a disaster. As the flowing water got louder, he felt hopeful that he would find his way back to camp until all of a sudden he was falling. Splash! He hit the water hard after a 5 second free-fall. Smashing his head on the bottom of the waterfall, he descended into darkness.

Captain Blackeye was in strange position. He had dedicated his life to the Royal Navy, and had served his country heroically, yet he was about to embark on a strange new adventure witha a ratag group of pirates. None of them could be considered friends. There was Rufus "Snakehead" McGraw, a fearsome pirate renowned for biting his enemies like a snake, Gregor Jones, a young orphan, who was there as he had no where else to go, and Sir Edward Wolpole, an elderly gent who nobody could understand had turned up.     Their mission was to go where no other group of sailors had dared to go before - the Font of Desire. It was suere to be a dangerous mission across the seven seas filled with all sorts of monsters. However, it was a mission that would undoubtedly make legends of any victors - living or dead. Captain Blackeye straightened his cap "All right Lads, let's begin"!

Three friends set out on a daring adventure across the seemingly endless open seas, facing unpredictable weather and battling ravenous sea creatures. Their deep bond grows as they rely on each other's strength and wit to guide them through treacherous waters in search of a mysterious, legendary island. As they finally reach their destination, they uncover a stunning treasure. This treasure was called the one piece and with it the three friends could finally locate the legendary island they had been looking for. Juan, the 'captain' of the crew knew what to do with the one piece as his grandfather had told him many stories about it. He grabbed hold of the treasure, which looked like a sort of puzzle piece, and slotted it into a special spot he had carved out on the table in the ships hull. The entire table began to glow and somehow, as if there was a hidden projector in the table, an image appeared on the ceiling. This image showed an Island and a very clear red cross, it also showed everyone where they were in real time and the distance from the red cross in Miles.

One day there were three men hanging around in the jungle. Each boy had a task they needed to complete. The first man needed to build a bridge over a deep ravine. The second needed to get a rock from the top of the tallest hill. The third had to fetch water from a crocodile infested lake. They set about their tasks with haste but also trepidation. As each man was half way through their task, they all came to the same realisation that they had no idea who set these tasks and what their purpose was. They all decided to return to each other and celebrated in the fact that they had no bosses as they were men of the jungle and were free to do what they wanted.

In the year 3045 a group of daring time travellers embarked on their most ambitious mission yet. Their goal was to witness the birth of the universe but a malfunction in the time and space co-ordinates sent them on their way to an unknown part of space in an unknown part of time. Instead of witnessing te Big Bang they found themselves stranded on an distant and strange planet, unlike anything they had ever known. The air was alien with an unkown scent and the sky shimmered with hues never seen before. The atmosphere was breathable and the explorers bagan to explore the strange terrain. As night fell they looked up into the night sky and realised something strange: there were no stars. The night was as black as could be, their only light coming from what appeared to be luminous rocks scattered around. They were curious and one of them picked up two rocks and smashed them together which resulted in an almighty flash of light and a bang!

Matthew turned to John and said "I think we should head towards the North now"....John was not happy about this as he thought he was a better seafarer than Matthew. They had come this far to find hidden treasures, but the darkness was coming in, and the sea was wild and unforgiving. Matthew was not happy with John's response, but John did as he was asked to. "You know that mum and dad are worried sick about us doing this" don't you Matthew. Matthew turned away from John, he just needed him to have a little faith in him on this journey of discovery

As the small group set sail from the harbour, Sasha realised that her life was in the hands of the people on board for the next week. It was a difficult concept for her to grasp as she was so used to being in control of her own life.  She just hoped that the weather would be kind to them and that they wouldn't have to face treacherous storms at sea as she wasn't a great sailor.  The group settled down into a routine where they each had their own tasks and jobs to do on board and the days passed quite quickly. The expedition was to find hidden treasure and they were expected to be out at sea for 7 days as long as the weather held. Sasha was working in the galley kitchen and was providing food and sustenance to the divers who were looking for the treasure. The evenings were spent quietly after all the work had been done and the divers were tired after their exertions, but Sasha found comfort from talking to all the people from different walks of life that she would never normally have met. She found her own treasure was the friendship and camaraderie on board and had made friends for life during her time on the boat.

Three bold, adventurous astronauts departed Earth on a mission to uncover life on a newly discovered planet. They left behind everything they'd ever known with no idea when or if they would return, but they did it in the name of science. The journey was long and arduous, but they hoped everything they discovered would make it worthwhile. As they arrived on the small, rocky planet, they realised just how far away they were from home. Everything looked strange and new, and they felt a deep sense of unease as they considered that not every creature in this world would be friendly. As they began to explore, they uncovered strange landscapes, astonishing lifeforms and ancient ruins, and it isn't long before they stumble across a powerful secret that will forever alter their perception of the universe. The astronauts must now choose whether to share their revelation with the world or keep the planet's mysteries for themselves. The captain sits down in front of the monitor, their only connection to planet EartH, and makes his decision.

Bob and Alice are playing on the beach one day when they spot a small wooden boat at the water's edge. There are two paddles inside and Alice suggests to Bob that they get in the boat and take it out on the water, Bob is unsure "it might be dangerous" he says to Alice, but Alice dares him to do it so he agrees and they push the boat out in to the water and get in it. Paddling furiously against the incoming waves their excitement gets the better of them and by the time they stop to look back they are a long way from the shore. "I'm scared," Alice says to Bob, "we should turn back now", but Bob is excited now and says "no, let's keep padding and see how far we can get". A few minutes later the shore is now so distant it is hardly visible and even Bob is starting to get a bit scared so they agree to turn back but it is too late, the boat is caught it a strong current and is being drawn further from the shore; even paddling as fast as they can, Bob and Alice cannot make progress against the current and as their arms tire they stop padding and just let the boat drift where it will. As it starts to go dark the temperature drops and they huddle together to keep warm, wondering where they will end up as tiredness gets the better of them and they start nod off. Suddenly they are woken from their semi-sleep by a loud noise and a lurching of the boat and realise they have hit something; Bob gropes around by the side of the boat and feels hard rock: "Quick Alice, we've hit land, let's get out of the boat!" They climb out on to the rock and feel their way up away from the water, relieved to be on land but wondering where on earth they have ended up.

In the heart of the dense jungle, a group of daring explorers embarked on an exhilarating adventure. Led by the fearless Johny, they ventured into the unknown, their spirits brimming with anticipation. Nature's symphony surrounded them as they treaded through dense foliage. Majestic creatures and treacherous terrain tested their mettle. Together, they forged an unbreakable bond, bound by the thrill of discovery. Lost in time, they unearthed ancient ruins, unravelling hidden secrets. They embraced the wild with each step. In the end, their journey through the jungle became an unforgettable chapter in their lives.

In search of an ancient treasure, a mighty crew embarks on a thrilling adventure across the Indian Ocean, battling treacherous storms and skilled pirates. As they navigate mysterious islands and decode cryptic symbols, their bond and loyalty begin to be tested by greed and deception. The captain is aware some of his crew are not on the ship for the thrill of the adventure, but rather for the potential wealth they might accrue from the treasure. On one dark night, the ship is attacked by a group of pirates, and the crew rises to the occasion. Forgetting their differences, everybody fights tooth and nail for the survival of their ship. The team emerges victorious, and in taking over the pirates' ship, they discover additional maps that could help them reach the treasure. Decoding the newfound clues, they are overwhelmed with joy and their ability to work together grows even more robust. Ultimately, they discover the true meaning of friendship and claim both treasures, the material one and the legacy they left behind that would inspire generations to come.

It seemed that the planet had been lived on before. There was evidence of former life and the astronauts all looked at each other in shock. "we should get out of here" one of them proclaimed. As they began to turn to leave the area a large shadow appeared behind them. They turned to look at what it was to find a tiny purple creature looking up at them. Due to the positioning of the sun on this planet, the creatures size was hugely out of proportion. It squeaked and ran under a nearby rock. The astronauts gently went over to investigate.

In a distant galaxy's infinite expanse, the inteprid crew of the starship Endeavor embarked on a perilous mission to explore an uncharted planet. Their vessel descended into a vibrant atmosphere, its alien colours swirling beneath them. Landing gently, they emerged onto an unknown terrain, where towering flora loomed like ancient sentinels. As they ventured deeper, they encountered a mesmerising civilization of bioluminescent 'tech-styled' ancient beings. Communicating in a harmonious melody of light and sound. With wide-eyed wonder, they learned the secrets of interstellar travel and the importance of harmony between al life forms. Reluctantly bidding farwell, they left the celestial utopia, taking with them newfound wisdom, hope and a shared vision of unity that would forever shape their own world. Returning home, they vowed to protect their planet, cherishing the memories of their extraordinary encounter, a testament to the infinite possibilities awaiting those who dare to venture beyond the stars.

A young boy was flying with his parents over to Brazil when the plane was hijacked. The hijackers had caused an explosion resulting in the boy being flung out of the plane and knocked unconscious. He woke up to a group of explorers standing around him. It turns out that he had landed on thick bush trees in the jungle which had cushioned his fall down and these explorers were looking for ancient civilization ruins. With nowhere else to go, he joins them on this adventure through an unknown land with various dangers. A couple days later, the boy stumbles and knocks over a tree, which reveals a stone pillar behind it. This causes the group to explore the area around them. They explore the area and find that there is a gigantic tree and within this tree is a temple, and through the hieroglyphs they find it is called the temple of freedom.

On a dark  night in the jungle, the group of friends find themselves completely lost. With only one torch left working, they must rely on eachoethers skills to find their way back to their village. They encounter many obstacles along their way, including snakes, spiders and even other humans trying to stop them from entering a forbidden old ruin. After discovering what looks like ancient relics the race is on to return the artifacts back to civilization before they are lost forever. The group soon realise that what they find will change not only their lives but history itself. I tale of suspence, adventure and friendship. The group learn to understand eachother on a deeper level and gain better relationships. They will be able to retell their tale for years to come.

Nancy had always wanted an adventure with her dog Daisy. They had grown up together and seemed to be so closely bonded and tuned in to one another. The boat looked small enough to handle but big enough to be able to be trustworthy at sea. After checking no-one was around, Nancy silently loaded the picnic, the sleeping bags and Daisy into the boat in the darkness. Nancy paddled out into the bay under the moonlight, watching the shapes in the water that the oars were creating. After a while, when out of sight, she started the engine, the way her Dad had taught her, and carefully headed towards the next bay. Nancy was up front with her front legs on the bench so gat a better view. The sea was flat calm and the moon was full - the best conditions for Nancy and Daisy's adventure on the open seas.

Florence would not say that she enjoyed nature exactly, but she kind of liked being alone in the jungle. Or at least, she thought she was alone. Wearing this headset made it difficult to appreciate what was real and what was not. Sounds suddenly invading her consciousness and brief, wraith-like images flickering at the edge of her vision. What here is imagined and what is real; how much of what she was experiencing was she herself generating? She would not know for sure for another 59 minutes and eight seconds...

You would never think they would be friends; they shouldn't be really - Ella, Cleo and Tinsel were a trio like no other. Ella a brave explorer, renowned across the world, Cleo a mischievous monkey who loved to prank, and Tinsel, who no one had ever heard of, but was the wisest of them all. On their journey to find the lost emerald of Arcadia, they encountered more than they could've ever imagined. The first day, Mount Fuli erupted, and lava cascaded down their hills they were camped on. Luckily, Tinsel's heat-proof shell saved the day and Cleo and Ella rode to safety on it. The second day, the ecountered a kraken, with tentacles bigger than a skyscraper. Luckily, it wasn't any match for Cleo who pranked their way out of it, with a decoy ship. By day three, they decided perhaps it wasn't worth their while anymore and the only treasure they needed was each other.

I was once on a hot air balloon ride over the amazon rainforest. A flock of birds got caught up in the balloon and sent us tumbling down through the trees. We landed in a clearing with only minor injuries, their were 4 of us, and we had enough supplies for roughly 2 days. Luckily we had an emergency satellite phone which also had gps tracking so we were able to call for help. The help would take about a day to arrive given how deep into the jungle we were and the locals did not have further air support to help us. It was quire scary wondering what dangerous animals could be lurking (big or small) I think I was more scared of the smaller ones to be honest. The ones that could be hiding under a leaf ready to kill you with one sting/bite. Help arrived in the end and we were all led back safely.

Captain Bilby had just arrived at the planet Zarg, home of the Zarglings, to negotiate a diplomatic treaty. He was looking forward to the mission, and flew down to the surface by shuttlecraft, where he was greeted warmly by the Zargling ambassador. However, trouble wasn't far behind when Captain Bilby's pet cat, Disco, tottered out of the shuttlecraft, having crept on to be part of the adventure! It turned out that the Zarglings didn't know what cats were, and thought the Captain had unleased a dangerous creature! Captain Bilby managed to explain the situation, whilst Disco looked on, completely oblivious to the diplomatic incident he'd nearly caused. The Zargling ambassador kindly offered Disco some of their local delicacy, baked He'Dash, a type of meat, and Disco wasted no time in eating the offered snack. The Zargling diplomats were very smitten with Disco, and wanted to pet him and watch his strange feline ways. Thanks in no small part to the Captain's cat, the diplomatic negotiations were a complete success, with Disco even being awarded the Zargling Medal of Freedom - their highest honour!

Bill was an old, experienced seadog. He had never known his boat to be compromised in this way. The hull had been opened up by the rough weather and seas. Bill knew he was alone and had to deal with this himself. He was in the middle of an expansive ocean. He had only a small dinghy and meagre rations and his radio did not work. He thought of what his family would think if he were not to return. He made the decision to cast off the dinghy and take his chances on the open sea.

The astronauts were exploring a new planet.    They saw a strange animal there.  They did not know what the animal was as they had never seen it before.  They faced the strange animal and it looked very fierce.  The astronauts decided  to stick together to defeat the animal.   As they worked together the animal stood  up and spoke.  It said "Welcome".  They thought this animal would be friendly and they all smiled.

John and Jack were lurking amongst the lobster buckets scattered around the harbour peeping through the gaps to see when was best to make there move, they saw the crew men speaking to the captain and took their chance. They ran quickly dodging the littered lobster buckets covered in seaweed, the smell of fish and sea salt in the air; they leapt onto the boat trying their best to make the landing as soft and quiet as possible.   They had made it!   Now they were on the boat they looked around swiftly for a place to hide till the boat launched, once they were out at sea they were safe to come out. Nobody could rid them off the boat when they were surrounded by miles and miles of water.   The boat horn sounded and the time had come, the boat was launching, knowing they were going to be safely far away from dry land and the dangers they had got themselves in filled John with an overwhelming feeling of relief. A few hours passed and they were in the middle of the sea, safe to come out and face the crew, they came out from their hiding place and the sea air hit them like a tonne of bricks.   "what are you too doing there" shouted a man from across the boat deck, they had been spotted already where they about to be taken back to shore and the danger they had just escaped?

an astronaut heads off to a distant planet.he does not know if it is inhabited as it is obscured by cloud.when he touches down safely he is relieved.on exploring he finds no signs of life,further exploration reveals tunnels under the surface.he enters them only to find they are empty.there is no life.reluctantly he reboards his ship & leaves.on returning to earth he reports his findings.

A spaceship carrying two brave astronauts journeys to a distant planet using the latest space technology available to mankind. Their purpose is to find new resources and perhaps even signs of life on a new planet which has been identified and studied by scientists. The journey is dangerous and requires the astronauts to travel further than anyone has ever been in space. The new planet has been named Verbon and the astronauts travel through many perilous space storms to get there. Upon arrival the astronauts see that Verbon is a colourful planet full of green and blue terrain, just like Earth. They manage to successfully land their ship and disembark to explore their surroundings. While exploring the astronauts come across what appears to be an unusual building and immediately feel that there is some form of life existing on this new planet. They immediately contact their colleagues back on earth to alert them of this unbelievably exciting new development.

Today we are leaving for a week adventure on a private boat on the open sea, everyone is very exited and looking forward to the trip. I will be going with my partner and friend and their partner. We have all packed and ready to leave, we get to the boat and get on board we set off into the ocean the sea is a little choppy at first but then it calms down. All of the sudden we see dolphins in the water along side the boat it was very exiting to see them. The evening arrives and we make dinner on the boat we had salad with prawns. The next few days go by and the waether has been great it has been very relaxing. On the last day we decide to go by a island to have a look it looks like no one lives there but is a beautiful place. Its the final day and we make our way home after a great week away on the open sea.

The band of pirates set off on their quest to reach the island of Cardonia. Their last trip to the island had not ended well as they were attacked by locals who had kidnapped six of their party and stolen their gold. The remaining pirates had barely escaped with their lives. However, having spent the last six months licking their wounds and regaining strength, they were back on a mission to rescue their friends and retrieve their treasure. The first difficulty was in finding the island. Previously they had stumbled on it by accident, after a storm had blown them off course.  Having consulted many maps of the surrounding seas they had discovered the island was not charted which increased the difficulty in locating it. At first they had thought it was an impossible task but then Jarn had come up with a plan.

Two friends embark on a thrilling journey through an uncharted jungle, seng a legendary ancient treasure deep within its depths. Encouraging dangerous creature's and overcoming treacherous obstacles, they discover the hidden city of gold and form a bond stronger than ever. The adventure ultimately changes their lives, providing valuable lessons about courage, friendship, and the true meaning of wealth. Upon return back to their hometown with the treasure many people around them became envious of the new found wealth.  the 2 friends then tried to share some of the weith with the town. many people wanted to take it for them selves  this lead the 2 friends to fight. After some time they went their separate ways.  they split the fortune and one of the friends left the town while the other stayed.

It was the 4th of July. We looked back towards earth as it faded to a small white dot. The journey was swift, 5 minutes later we were 15 light years away, approaching the unnamed planet. It was chosen as being similar to earth. As we disembarked, the purple sun set and we fell into a dream. It was misty, we were tired and then as tried to sleep we saw the earth explode, there would be no return. Then this new land became a new earth, and from us, the last 3 humans, angelic beings came and populated this new earth with a new humanity. We awoke and realised the dream had come true, was well and calm, planet Eden was the new paradise we had always longed for.

Steve had never flown in a plane before the day that changed him. After the crash and being thankful they were all still alive, Steve and his three friends knew they had to do anything to survive. They were lucky in a way, they had their backpacks and food enough for weeks if they were careful. However, being in the jungle was not ideal. There were predators here, and insects, also things that are unseen that could be worse. Unclean water for instance. But still, they were only scratched up a little and had their GPS transponders,  surely help would be on the way soon. They set about making their camp, first building a fire and then moving on to shelter that was off the jungle floor.

Earth has finally passed the climate tipping point and civilisation is starting to collapse, with large areas of the planet having become uninhabitable and those parts that are still tolerable, deteriorating quickly, so it looks like there is only a relatively short period of time before life on Earth disappears completely.     Using recently developed, novel space drive systems that exploit the fabric of the universe to traverse wormholes almost instantaneously, thousands of explorers have been sent to search for likely new planets that humans could use as new homes.    Likely destinations have been identified using the results of work carried out by SETI, that catalogued many sources of extra-terrestrial signals, combined with data sent back from the Hubble and James Webb deep space telescopes.     Scientists have used all this to create a long list of destinations to explore.    Even using the space-drive breakthroughs, this work is likely to take decades, before anything is selected as  likely to be suitable, as the work involved at each of the sites will take years.    This work has come about only because the major economic powers of the world have finally agreed to work co-operatively, rather than in their individual national interests.    The world's dwindling population looks on in bewilderment and anger, as it struggles to survive on rationed resources and in worsening conditions.    If only world leaders had listened to the climate warnings issued decades ago.

A crew of divers, several of the best in the world are determined to plot the depths of the oceans of Venus. Though designated as a crew, these group of divers hate each other and are nothing like a crew in reality. The researchers knowing this, design the submarine to be exactly manned by the 8 divers. If one person dies (or is killed) the submarine would become inoperable. While the rest of the divers are fine with this clause, there exists a mad man amongst them. Who is he? Nobody knows. Join us in this murder whodunnit set in the depths of space, where the twist is each person does their best to make sure everyone comes out alive against the whims of a mad man.

Three friends (Mike, Elle and Kim) embark on a peaceful adventure into the depths of the jungle. They are fed up of city life and work and just want to get away from it all to recharge. After setting up camp in the jungle, Mike explores the area to find water and some branches to start a fire. After what seems like hours, Kim and Elle start getting worried as there is no sign of Mike and the darkness is beginning to fall. Luckily there is a full moon so the jungle is slightly lit which is lucky because Mike didn't take a torch. Whilst waiting, the girls fell asleep and awoke to find Mike's body just outside their tent. It looked like Mike had been attacked by a wild animal as he was covered in deep claw wounds and covered in blood. The girls had no means of communication as they had all left their phones at home so they armed themselves with sticks and went to find help.

The sea swelled with the rage more than the crewmates were used to.  Their sails bucked and billowed in the strong winds that were dragging them off course.  Fear crept into each nook, cranny, and fold of the clothes which adorned them.  The reality was setting in, the goal of which they set out toward just a few short months ago was, seemingly, closer than ever.  That is if their new navigator, and more importantly, his charts, did not lie.  The Bermuda Triangle, a famed expanse of open water between the colonies and the Carribbean.  Had all that were lost before them been on the hunt of the same thing, were their truths to the stories kept so hush?  Only time could tell if those brave men would find it or find death, the Isle of the Illuminatus.

On a planet called Gwappy there lived a land dolphin called Gwoimpy. Being a land dolphin, Gwoimpy could walk, obviously, though not gracefully. Sometimes other animals would snicker when Gwoimpy shuffled by, but Gwoimpy honestly didn't care. He was long in the tooth, so to speak, and had seen it all. However, even though he wasn't offended in any way by their sleight, he did feel that rudeness should be punished, for how else would they learn? So one bright and sunny day, Gwoimpy headed off to where he knew the snickerers would probably be, and as he was shuffling ungainly past them, he pulled out the machine gun that he kept in his large backpack, and sprayed them all with lead. They all died. Gwoimpy, the psychopathic land dolphin on Gwappy, lived happily ever after.

The sun dipped below the horizon, casting a warm golden glow on the vast expanse of the open sea. Peter and a group of young adventurers attempted a daring journey on the high seas, they consisted of a diverse group of travelers aboard the ship. This ship was called The Siren's, they knew they must bound together on this adventure because they might encounter a group of ruthless pirates and fierce storms. As they embarked on this thrilling journey towards the unknown sailing slowly and smoothly, night fell, the stars emerged guiding them through the dark waters.     Days turned into weeks as they sailed with courage and determination. They encountered treacherous storms that tested their resilience and calms that whispered tales of ancient mariners. Dolphins danced alongside their vessel, playful splashes bringing moments of joy and companionship. Through their adventure, they formed an unbreakable bond that lead them to a newfound understanding of friendship, trust and true meaning of wealth as the sailed peacefully and did not encounter any dangerous pirate.

Jack and Moi looked at each other. The look of fear and disbelief was written all over their faces. They stared at each other in what seemed an eternity but only microseconds. They looked around, slowly, looking at what used to be walls of the plane, but now gaping holes showing the jungle peaking through. They had survived the crash but what now? Alone, in a hostile jungle miles from civilisation with just their wits to survive. Jack unbuckled his belt and leant over to Moi to undo hers. "Lets go, we can do this, we will find help" he calmly told her despite his inner voice screaming that they will never make it.

He awakes in a glass tube, all he can see through the window is smoke. To his left is a red emergency button that he strikes, frantically till the door of the tube opens with a loud hiss.  "Where am I? Who am I? What happened? His memory loss from hypersleep begins to subside and he gazes through the window of the ship. he turns around, all of the other tubes filled with his crew mates, still frozen in time. He struggles with the pod controls but can't seem to get any of them to open, He takes a step back and thinks to himself "I never trained for this, I'm just the chef!

The explorers stepped off their ship and immediately were taken back by vibrant colors and alien sound of the new planet.  While exploring, they found an abandoned city with strange ruins unlike anything they had ever seen.  After exploring further, the trio came across a settlement of aliens,seemingly unaware of most of the universe beyond. The explores quickly explained  their plight to the aliens and the need to bridge the two civilians. Although hesitant, the aliens agreed and together they formed a partnership to tackle coming threats. As they prepared for the upcoming battle, the explores marveled at the beauty of the planet,hoping to on day bring lasting peace and friendship. They also made sure they have lost no contact of each other till mission accomplished. They collabo made a good company which helped in research and the general history of the visit.

Sarah lives with her dad on a lighthouse situated on a deserted island. Their job is to make sure the fishing ships that go by travel without any problems. Sarah sometimes feels very lonely living only with her dad and dreams of what its like in the city, but all she knows from her dad is that the city is dangerous, even more dangerous than the sea, and she isn't allowed to go there until she turns 18.   One day Sarah has an argument with her dad and decides to hide in one of shipping boats that brings deliveries to the them on the island. No one knows that Sarah was hidden in the boat. When the boat reaches the city Sarah gets so excited and starts exploring right away. But the problem is that Sarah has no money and no idea how to get around in such a big place, and she ends up getting lost. She goes around and around until she finds her cousin that recognises her straight away and calls her dad, Sarah tries to run away but her cousin stops her and tells her that its ok,explains to her that her dad is stopping her from coming here because its very dangerous and he cares about her very much, Sarah understands and agrees to come back but asks her cousin to ask her dad to let her come to the city with an adult at least, her cousin agrees, Sarah smiles happily.

Three friends embark on a new adventure through a dense, unexplored jungle in search of the lost city.  Along the way they face treacherous terrain, creatures never been seen before in their young lives. after many hours of travelling they discover a gap in small cave between two rocks, just wide enough to fit through. All three friends climb through the gap in the rocks without hesitation, what they discovered on the other side would change their lives forever. On the other side there wasn't a lost city it was thriving city with people living what seemed in a different time from what the three friends had been living. This lost city was beautiful and was at least 100 years in future from the real world. The three friends were excited, scared and curious all at the time asking themselves what just happen, looking back through the rocks they can still see the dense jungle real world they just left. Before long the friends realised the lost city they were searching for became a portal into the future.

Embarking on a journey to a far-away planet, a group of explorers seek to investigate the possibilities of extra-terrestrial life forms on a never-seen-before planet. Upon arrival, the team meet a strange-looking alien life form, who despite their look, are amicable and supportive to the team in aiding their navigation of such complex terrain. The aliens are the equivalent of humans on this strange planet world, so are full of wisdom and experience. Despite communication differences, their paralleled hospitality and kindness is received as progress towards interplanetary peace and cooperation. The astronauts encounter so many incredible creatures and landscapes in this thrilling adventure through their touring of the planet with the alien species. The group seek to return to Earth with this newfound knowledge in an attempt to aid SpaceCorp in investigating the possibilities of transporting humans to another planet in the midst of the climate crisis. However, the trio have extreme setbacks and challenges in navigating such complex terrain, and fear for their safety. Facing a power malfunction on their rocketship, and with the absence of power development on the planet, will they make it back to Earth alive or be stuck on the planet indefinitely?

A team of explores traveled to Solar, an unexplored planet. Solar was very hot with two suns, and rolling desert hills. The explores set up tents for the night. One explore, a girl named Luna was woken up by a strange growling noise. She went outside, and found a creature that looked a fox. It was completely red and glittered like rubies with two black almond shaped eyes and large pointed ears. The creature was very friednly and let Luna pet it. Luna could not wait to see what other wonders were on Solar.

visited a cage,the entrance was so low. with some beautiful trees around it. we went into it along with the cave guards. it was dark, we made use of torchlight. the view was so beautiful and astonishing. we heard noises of bats. we moved from one section of the cave to another. certain sections we had to craw to get in . the experience was very exciting

The group nervously waited in their hut for the guide to arrive, they had been delivered to the location two days previously and had little idea of why they were there.   The advert on instagram had asked for volunteers for a charitable project and thinking it would add an extra sting to the bow of their gap year CV the youngsters had all jumped at the chance.   After a long and hot wait a small slightly bedraggled man appeared signaling to the group to follow.
