Silently the teens obediently filed behind him into the dense undergrowth each internally questioning their passivity.  They trekked and trekked for hours and soon the sights and sounds of the unfamilar environment started to dull and heat and thirst took over.   A sense of panic grew amongst the group; where was the end point, what was the purpose.   Eventually they arrived at a hut and hot and thirsty they were given water, some kids were shaking and muttering, not making sense even to themselves.   Ae they lay on the floor confused, scared and weak they were jolted awake by the flashes and sounds of the cameras and lights and the greeting of the TV host.

The jungle was full of lush, green vegetation and the sounds of the animals could be heard, like a cacophny of sound. It was difficult for the explores to find their way through but, in the distance, the golden tip of a building could be glimpsed. The friends hurried towards it as fast as their tired and wearly limbs would take them. It was a temple! As silently as possible, the friends opened the door of the temple and peered inside. Tom, the oldest of the explorers, took it upon himself to enter and called out a hesitant 'hello' into the dark. However, all that was waiting for them inside was dust and the feeling of age-old secrets, long forgotten. The explorers sighed and turned their exhausted bodies to leave when, all of a sudden, Tom let out a gasp of excitment; hidden in the dust, there was a box!

Davy was a pirate that sailed the high seas. He and his band of mates visited and sailed around many continents and Oceans. One day their ship was attacked by Orca Whales. They found this very unusual as they had seen Whales many times before but had never had any issues and always felt safe around them. The Whale attacks disabled the rudder on the ship which left them unable to steer the vessel. They were stranded in the ocean for days and were unable to move. Davy and his mates began to get hungry and argued about how they would obtain food and water. Just as they were about to lose hope, the Whales returned and again attacked the ship but after this attack the rudder was somehow working again.

Three friends embark on a journey into the unexplored depths of the jungle, navigating treacherous terrain and overcoming unforeseen challenges. Their once in a lifetime adventure ultimately leads to an astonishing revelation about the origins of the lost civilization they've uncovered. They are the first people to set eyes on this lost civilization since it was inhabited yet there is still a spooky feeling they are feeling that they are being watched. They decide to leave the area and retreat as quickly as they can, but it is to no avail. No matter how quickly they try to run they simply cannot move their feet. Eventually exhausted they collapse to the floor and all go to sleep unable to keep their eyes open. They awaken several hours later out of the jungle and back in their own beds at home. Was this all a dream or what happened and will they ever find out the truth?

On a mysterious newly discovered planet, a group of fearless explorers embarked on an exhilarating adventure to discover the planet's unique flora and fauna. It was not as easy as they had hoped as every new experience comes with unseen dangerous obstacles. As they delved deeper into this new uncharted world, they uncovered relics from long-lost advanced civilizations, that seemingly vanished without a trace. The aim of the explorers was to find a planet similar to Earth. The reason is that the earth has been polluted for years and they fear it may become inhabitable. This is not the first planet they had explored as the previous attempts to find an Earth-like planet has been unsuccessful. They were hoping this would be a success but unfortunately, there were so many unsolved puzzles left behind that needed to be uncovered. The explorers must solve these quickly as time is running out and people on Earth depend on them.

I woke slowly, drowsy and unsure. My head was wet and my left ear was cold. I turned to the left and got a faceful of water. My head had been in a muddy puddle, and this caused me to sit bolt upright ,started and now scared.  I immediately realised how humid it was and I could hear rain falling ,yet not hosting the ground around me. The puddle was in the middle of a track that cut through the trees and undergrowth that formed my surrounding.  There was a vehicle on the edge of the track about fifty yards away ,half in a ditch to the edge, and with the back door open.  I recognised the backpack that I could see sticking out of the door as my own, but not the body of the person,  bleeding and either dead or very close to it ,that now lay across my luggage.

Two astronauts go to the previously unexplored planet Gritzup. Things are not as they seem on this planet, everything is glowing. The trees are bright pink on appearance but once you get up close they go dark. The astronauts spot a peculiar looking being coming towards them. The alien greets them and welcomes them to his planet. The alien asks if the astronauts can help him save his planet. It is under threat from another planet and they must solve mysteries to complete their mission. The astronauts complete their missions and the planet is saved.

During a voyage to a new newly discovered planet, a team of scientists find an alien species that speak an unknown language. There was a degree of hostility to begin with, but luckily the advanced technology the aliens possess resulted in communication. Having established a dialogue, the aliens were willing to share their technology with the scientists. The scientists were quickly engulfed by what can only be described as mechanic tentacles which wrapped around their bodies. they instantly understood everything the alien species had to offer. They improved their space crafts efficiency to over 300% and headed back to earth. Upon returning to earth they debated how this new technology would be received. When they landed back at NASA HQ they were quarantined and then shot.

Captain Sirius and his team land on Primus-Five, crashing through a thick layer of clouds which is obscuring their vision and sensors. After landing and finding a place to set up their basecamp, they are greeted by a lush green paradise and weird unerving noises.    They immediately set out to explore Primus-Five, which they discover is home to a rich history and culture evidenced by ancient ruins and artifacts that litter this planet. Soon after exploring they encounter a hostile alien species that have inhabited the planet for a long time but are able to communicate with the astronauts.    Captain Sirius reveals he is not interested in finding a planet to live co-existing with another species, instead he just wants to exploit Primus-Five for it's natural resources. He has a secret weapon on the ship which is designed to kill everything already on the planet and seeks support from his crew.    A crew member decides to stop Captain Sirius, and finds the weapon. They realise to destroy the weapon and save the planet, they will have to go on a one way suicide mission in a pod to space to detonate it which they dutifully do.

Rita has always felt out of place on Earth, as if she belonged somewhere else in the universe that is waiting for her. So when the opportunity came to assemble a small but diverse percentage of the population to go on a spaceship to reach Earth2 and populate it, Rita had no hesitation to apply. Earth2 had been found just a few years ago, and to scientists it seemed to provide extremely similar conditions to the first of its name and plans were made to make this journey possible, including developing technology that would allow to make the travel in 1 month while it is 100 light years away. Passengers were only allowed to bring a small suitcase which was no issue to Rita that filled it with 4 different changes of clothes, 3 favourite books, 2 cds and 1 harmonica. There was no one that cared enough about Rita or that she cared about them, to say goodbye so on the day of the departure she was one of the few that wasn't teary eyed and as excited as one possibly can be. There would be 4 identical spaceships that looked almost as if a cruise on the inside, but Rita spend her month just looking out the window, avoiding conversation with anyone, playing her harmonica and trying to see if she could feel any connection with the planets they would see along the way in hope to get a clue of her identity. When the day of arrival came, Rita was disappointed with Earth2. It looked exactly like what she had been trying to escape, and so months would go by with the same feeling that there has to be something out there for her, more than Earth or Earth2.

Bob: Did we come this way before ?  Ronald: I don't think so  Bob: That constalation looks rather familiar  Ronald: They all look the same to me!  Bob: Whats for supper?  Ronald: Don't ask me Ask Daisy  Bob: DAISY WHATS FOR SUPPER?   Daisy: Its a surprise....

Declan was scared.  He knew this would be his one chance to prove to his parents he was not a loser and make them proud.  He looked at his map and compass for the tenth time in the last 2 minutes as the boat swayed from side to side, rising and falling as each wave crashed against the side.  He thought of home and playing with his mates on his playstation.  This was for real.  This was not Fornite or the Metaverse. How he wished he could just log out and switch off this experience and try again tomorrow. No, he must perservere onwards to the end of the challenge, alone with no friends to chat to.

I was born on the south coast and everyday i watched boats go out to sea. I always wanted to go on one but it seemed that I would never have the chance. But one day a friend asked me if I would like to join him on a trip to France. I was very excited, and said Yes. We planned the trip carefully, or so we thought, and left early one morning. However. strong winds got up and blew us onto a sandbank. We had to radio for help and eventually we were rescued and towed back to land.

Sarah's brother, Ted, had always wanted to be a sailor and dreamed of sailing across from Europe to the Caribbean. When Ted died tragically after falling off his bike, Sarah found a map he had drawn when he was thirteen detailing the journey he would make when he was twenty-one. As Sarah approached her twennty-first birthday, she decided she would complete the voyage in memory of Ted and acquired a boat which she named Teddy's Dream. Setting out from Portugal, she set sail into the open seas, with Ted's map, for a journey that would take her four months. At first, the seas were calm and she found the experience enjoyable and easy. But three weeks into the trip, she started experiencing problems and when a storm blew in, it damaged part of the boat and knocked out all communication. Sarah was left drifting on the seas in a damaged boat and without any way of calling for help. Just when Sarah was beginning to worry about what might happen to her, a humpbacked whale breached the sea next to her and seemed to be directing her onwards, it was then that Sarah remembered Ted's favourite animal was a humpback whale and she followed the animal as it led her to the Caribbean.

Nola disembarked from the spacecraft, elation and terror so potent that all she could focus on was the rapid beating of her heart. She had finally made it to the planet Kroger. The journey had been long and treacherous but now that she could see the characteristic rocky terrain and the blood-orange sky of the alien planet, she began to weep with joy and relief. The journey before her would be long and hard - but she had only one chance to rescue her brother from the space pirates and she was determined to succeed. She could still remember the ashen look on his face as he was captured and the way he screamed for her to help him. She could not help him then, but she would not fail him again. Trembling, Nola stepped onto the planet surface, gazing out at the horizon before closing her eyes. Clutching her map to her chest, she vowed: "I will find you".

In order to prevent climate catastrophe, a team of astronauts is sent from Earth to explore the outer solar system and find a new home. There are disagreements within the team as to how to complete the mission. The team breaks into groups of 2 or 3 and each explore their own choices of worlds. One team finds a cold inhospitable moon. The other team finds a hot, tropical moon. The teams cannot agree on which is best, so each faction decides to set up base on their own moon. Many years pass and the teams lose contact with each other. After many struggles, they meet again and decide to return to Earth.

The dolphin broke the surface of the simmering grey sea, the grey of its back almost imperceptible against the slate of the sky.  Its presence brought comfort to Eland's as his boat ploughed through the waters, waking a bow wave for the dolphins pleasure.    It had been hard running away from the mob, who challenged what he had done in the revolt. Nevermind what had forced him into it. But now he had questions of his own he had to answer. Who was he really, why was he at the center of all this chaos. And more importantly who was his Creaidh, who appear to be bound up in this saga as much as him. Just how many journeys appeared to be going on at once.

The adventure began here, I was wondering into the jungle, in search of something treasured, something valuable something no-one had ever come across before, the emerald egg. I had been on my hunt for many years now but all the clues lead here, to this very jungle. It wasnt going to be easy though. I trenched the jungle for days, my shoes became wet from the rainfall, I smelt and I was growing tired, especially after being on the lookout for dangerous animals. I was growing very tired, but my determination was strong, I had been through so much to be here, I was going to prove the non believers wrong and I was going to be rich too. I was thinking of setting up camp soon, but thats when I heard sounds in the distance. It sounded like humans, but it wasn't in any language I understood, but I decided to make my way over to the sounds. When I reached the destination, thats when I saw it the people, were crowded but in the middle of them the chief was holding the emerald egg!

The thrill-seeking astronomer, Max, embarks on a dangerous solo journey to Kepler-22b. The planet is unexplored and full of hostile alien creatures. Max must not only battle these creatures, but also the harsh weather conditions and the loneliness of space. Even the journey to Kepler-22b is fraught with peril. En-route, Max suffers disaster that causes him to lose most of his supplies. On arrival, he needs to create a camp and find sustenance. Max is attacked by various life forms and must hold them off with his ship's defence system. Max is overwhelmed and his last dying thought is why he bothered.

The Ship was battling against the aggressive tides of the sea. The Captain was yelling for his crew to prepare and brace for any sudden impacts. As they were sailing, a stray pirate ship bashed into them. As the stray ship hit theirs, the pirates boarded the captain's ship looking for him. The captain and the crew weren't going down without a fight, they got their weapons and started to defend themselves and the ship. From the look of it, the captain and his crew had the upper hand and had the pirates on their last leg until, one of the captain's crew members stabbed the captain in his back, not enough to kill him but enough to keep him grounded. The opportunity that the traitorous crewmate created gave the pirate crew enough time to turn the tables on the main crew. The captain was on his knees dumbfounded and shocked that his first mate would turn on him, but turns out the first mate was actually the captain from the group of pirates that boarded their ship, before the captain could get a word out, he was knocked out by one of the pirates.

The man and his friend decided they wanted to visit Mars. A few people will be required for the trip but it will be the first time a human has been on Mars. It might be a scary journey. However, if we are successful this could spark a new era for humanity. There will be a new scenery also we might find life. Although i don't think there will be any aliens on Mars. Nonetheless it will be an exciting trip. Hopefully, we all come back alive.

We were sailing across the sea, it was a lovely day and could see for miles. All of a sudden there was a shout from the captain , look over board a pirate ship is approaching. We all looked round in shock minutes earlier it was all clear now , a big ship approached with the scull and crossbones flying high in the sky. Terror started to kick in , would they shoot a cannon and sink us, or might they board the ship and make us all walk the plank .There was nothing we could do but wait in fear as the dreaded pirate ship got closer and closer.     The pirate ship came along side the bow, we could see no one about , then all of a sudden children ran out in all sorts of clothes looking like pirates , but not as scary as the real thing. Hello there shouted a lad of about 14 we need your help we need to take on some water then we will be on our way. The relief that came over our boat was amazing , and the young crewed pirate ship was scary , but exciting addition to our day.

There was a man named James who dreamed about going to another planet.  When he was young all he did was draw pictures of spaceships and dream about traveling into space and landing on a new planet.  James didn't know how he would get into space as he didn't have a spaceship nor could he fly a spaceship.    Every night before bed James would pray to the heavens for a space ship to take him to a new planet.  This went on for many years and still no spaceship would be there in the morning when he woke up or when he came home from school.  Then one day out of the blue James woke up and he heard a rumble, He ran down stairs and to his amazement, There it was a great big blue spaceship. He couldn't believe his eyes.    Within 30 minutes James was packed up and ready to go he said goodbye to his family  and pressed the big red button that said "launch" After some time he arrived on his new planet, He loved it so much that he decided to stay there forever.

Three people are stranded in the middle of a gigantic ocean, in a small emergency dingy. The boat they were on capsized and they have been adrift for several days. There are two men and one woman in the dingy and they have all been friends for many years. They have some supplies of food and a mechanism to turn seawater into fresh drinking water, so currently there is not too much stress about supplies. They have started talking about the possibility of death and that one or more of them may not survive. The weather has been on their side with calm waters and still nights - the moon radiating reflected light over the waters at night. Sometimes at night, they have been in awe at the night sky, seeing all the stars in the universe. This made them feel rather insignificant in the scheme of things - and helped them put to rest some of their unaddressed issues. Then, on the seventh day of them being adrift, a large passenger vessel caught sight of them, and brought them aboard - their lives to continue on with their adventures

Susan gazed at the foreign landscape, her heart pounding with excitement. The air crackled with unfamiliar energy, and the vibrant colors of the alien flora mesmerized her.  She took a hesitant step forward, her boot stinking into the lush, emerald grass. As she explored further, strange creatures darted through the trees, their iridescent wings shimmering in the sunlight. A gentle breeze carried the scent of exotic flowers, filling her senses. The sky above revealed celestial wonders unknown to Earth, with heavenly bodies dancing in a cosmic ballet. Susan's heart swelled with a sense of wonder and adventure, as she realized she was the first human to set foot on this extraordinary planet. At that moment, she knew she had embarked on a journey that would change her life forever, one filled with discovery, challenges, and the limitless possibilities of the universe.

In the heart of a dense jungle, a group of daring explorers embarked on an epic adventure.  With each step, the humid air clung to their skin, and the chorus of exotic creatures filled their ears.  Armed with their trusty machetes, they carved a path through the towering foliage, uncovering ancient ruins of a forgotten civilisation.  As they went deeper into the wilderness, their senses heightened, anticipating the unknown.  Mysterious sounds echoed through the trees.  Amidst the perils and the thrill, they found hidden treasures.  The sun dipped below the horizon, casting a glow on the trees, reminding them that their adventure had only just begun.  Who knows what waits.

A group of scientists from planet earth travels to a far away plant Virgo.  Their mission is to find resources that could b used on planet Earth.  Their journey turns out to be an exciting adventure full of twists and turns.  They arrive on planet Virgo and accidentally awake an alien civilisation and have to try and learn to communicate with these aliens when their spaceship crashes and they need help getting home.    They make friends, enemies and have the time of their lives.  The learn about themselves, their friends and the world around them.  Their journey opens their eyes to just how small we really are.  And just how big an adventure awaits you when you step outside your comfort zone.

The Jungle was hot and sticky.   The journey had been tough but the prize would be worth it.   A few more thrashes with the machete should do it.   Yes, the clearing.  The bottle is here.  Out with the stopper.  Give it a rub.  'Pleased to meet you Madame Jeanie.'

The Jungle is an unforgiving place and after thrashing through it for two days we were exhausted. We were running out of water and had no food left things were looking grim.   Just as we were about to give up we stumbled across a small stream, and our hearts lifted. We followed it, and the stream grew wider, eventually joining a large river. Looking around, we found a large tree trunk, which we managed to drag to the river and use as a flotation aid.   After floating downstream for what seemed like hours we were found by some indigenous people in canoes. The smiled a lot, and we were elated, thinking we had cheated death. Leading us to a clearing in the jungle, a man pointed at a large metal cauldron suspended over a fire "Climb in please" he said rubbing his tummy.

Rumours grow of a map that has recently been unearthed by the Queen's Scholars. The thief; a young, fearless captain, desperate to keep his band of men together aboard his ship, after years of failed treasure hunts. His ragtag crew embark on a treacherous journey across the uncharted ocean. Their aim is to uncover a long-lost, legendary treasure that relates to the Kings of the Old Kingdom. Their adventure is lined with deadly storms, menacing sea creatures, and pirate foes who also seek the treasure.  Many are lost on this journey, whether falling in combat, or through illness. Through courage, determination and unshakeable bond, they overcome the odds, finding not only the treasure but also the true meaning of friendship and bravery. While the treasure may bring riches, it is often said that the treasures of old should be left in the past, of the ancient and powerful magicks hidden insight might not lay dormant forever.

After travelling several years through space with my family, we finally arrived on the newly discovered planed named Cygnus X. We are all so excited what this new adventure brings but also anxious what we will encounter and discover. Upon embarking from our space ship we straight away discover intelligent alien life. These aliens seem friendly but also apprehensive of us but after a few weeks of setting up camp they got to know us a bit better and we started to trust us. Over the many months we explored the surrounding areas of our camp. And became friends with the aliens. One day we set off to explore the planet further with our new friends. After travelling a while we encountered something surprisingly and dangerous.

The jungle was dark and dangerous. It was home to many of the most fearsome and deadly animals - snakes as thick as trees, panthers that can track their prey for miles, spiders that can kill with a bite. So the jungle is was the last place we would have chosen for our plane to crash. The trees were so thick that no rescue helicopter would be able to find us, so we had no choice but to get out of here ourselves. We found a map, a compass and a little food and water in the plane - it was all we had to make trip to safety. As we made our way through the undergrowth, the sun beating down on us and the air thick with humidity we thought we would never make it. But eventually we came to the edge of the jungle and in the distance could see signs of civilization. We had made it.

When my mother finally decided to allow my brother and I to go exploring alone, we headed for the  Jungle. We had been there a few times before but only with a responsible adult. It was with great trepidation that we packed our backpacks with drinks and food and waved goodbye , with the promise to be home in time for tea.  Cautiously we walked the way we had been before then Ben my brother decided , as he was the eldest that we should take another direction which he was sure it would lead to the waterfall. His idea was that we could swim and have lunch and perhaps take some photos to take back and show Mum. For once he was right but as we approached we heard an almighty crash followed by loud scream screaming.  We froze and hid behind  a bush and listened. As we peered through the leaves both of us shaking with fear expecting to see our worst nightmare, a murder at least, then it became clear. A film crew in action

Callum and his sister Beth had travelled to many planets with their mother as part of an exploratory mission. There were twelve other teenagers on the ship and they had grown up with each other, experiencing the thrill and dangers of space travel together. As they got older their parents allowed them to take part more in their work. The first time they actually got to do this was on a previously unknown planet called Xephyr . The aliens living on Xephyr were curious to meet the crew and their families and Callum and Beth found that their teenage equivalent on Xephyr were not that different from themselves and they enjoyed making new friends . However, the next uncharted planet was very different...

There once was a pirate ship that set sail on the high seas to hunt for a great treasure. There was something special about this ship and her crew though and that was it was crewed by only monkeys but captained by a snake! Of course as you can imagine this mix of crew did not bode well for the success of their mission. The trouble started as soon as they left port because of course the crew had no idea how to operate the ship! The captain being a snake could only hiss his instructions which the monkeys did not understand and they continued to just play around and eat all the supplies. After a few weeks of sailing aimlessly the ship ran a ground on a deserted island. Fortunately for the monkeys and the snake there was plenty of food and water for them on this island so they decided to make this their home. And this is how what we know now as the country called England was started.

every time max left for his work week he felt the same dread.he had known all along that being in the navy,being a sailor was going to be hard. but he hadnt counted on commander henry,the ship master being so downright cruel and nasty to every cadet he took a disliking to.luckily max had just finished his leave of 3 weeks and was feeling positive about the next 6 weeks at sea.his mates craig and dennis were coming back to shiphe was keen to have a drink and a catch up.he hated leaving his parents. but thats what he had to do.little did he know he would never see his parents again.

Once upon a time, on a faraway planet called mimbo, there was a majestic place with lots of green forests and sparkly lakes. One evening, a group of brave explorers, led by the bravest person named nova,decided to go on an amazing dangerous adventure. They wanted to find the special glass of Eternity, and it was hidden in an old place called the Temple of shadows. They had to go through big mountains and it was extremely cold, but they kept going, as there was not turning back.They had a map that helped them, and they even survived a giant sandstorm of silica rain. Finally, they arrived at the door of the temple, which was surrounded by huge crooked statues guarding it. Upon the doors opening the glass shined bright, They knew they had to protect it.They realized that their journey was just beginning and they has to stay together and unit to save mimbo.

The year is 2123 and over-consumption of Earth's natural resources has created a barren landscape in rural areas, with most of Earth's population flocking to large cities where the few remaining resources are stockpiled.  Dwindling traditional forms of energy generation, such as oil, coal, and water, has created a desperate need to find an alternative energy source to power these gargantuan metropolises. In a daring mission to solve this growing issue a group of fearless astronauts embark on an unpredictable adventure to the planet Xyrus.  Battling extraterrestrial creatures, overcoming harsh climates, and deciphering strange symbols to unlock ancient secrets, they discover a powerful energy source that could change life as we know it.  The team stoically battle their way across the planet, back to their ship, facing staunch resistance from the native Xyrian population.  They reach their ship just ahead of the Xyrian defenders, but there isn't enough time for the team to board and take-off before they are overrun.  In a last ditch attempt to ensure the success of the mission, the team's commander, Mac, hangs back and sacrifices himself to give the rest of team a chance of survival.   Due to Mac's heroism, the remaining team manage to take-off and, after a long journey through the vast expanse of space, they arrive back on Earth to find the technologically superior Xyrian ships waiting for them!

in the heart of the Atlantic Ocean, the sun cast its golden rays open our ship named the Conqueror. A captain named Morgan stood at the head of the ship guiding us through the open seas. With howling wind and a sense of boundless freedom, we embarked on an epic adventure. Our quest was to uncover a legendary hidden treasure chest on the island of Nantucket. The salty air around us carried whispers of lost souls as our crew encountered heavy turbulence on our journey. Yet, our determination never wavered. Once the sunset and the moonlight appeared we followed the guidance of the twinkling constellations to our destination. We finally arrived at the ancient island after days of travelling, it was beautiful beyond belief.

Once upon a time a group of colleague sailors unexpectedly discovered a hidden treasure map. They gathered and discussed a plan to find the hidden treasure. They decided to embark on a sailing trip to venture the open seas and recover the old lost treasure, in the hope that they would be rich. Finally, they prepared for the trip and navigated the storms, defeated the villains and faced their fears in the pursuit for the treasure. It was clear that the group deeply cared for each other and value the team work. It was during this trip that they realized the true value of wealth and appreciated the bond and strong friendship that they have developed. Although, they weren't able to find a treasure in the form of metal and gold, they find a forever lasting friends. In the end, they had to return with loads of good memories to talk about for years.

Tarris was a small planet in the furthest point of the interstellar system, know for its beautiful beaches, stunning mountains and lakes, and breathable atmosphere, but also a most deadly species which lives below the ground and comes out at night.  Max and Sarden had been sent to Tarris with, food supplies and a team of andriods to secure the main tourist facility and rescue any survivors after it had been breached by the nocturnal beasts. The arrival on Tarris was not uneventful, with the space pod being tossed around by freak atmospheric storms resulting in its landing outside the tourist compound, some 20 clicks away, and night closing in fast.  Max and Sarden were fearful for their chances, but set up the android soldiers around the pod to watch and protect throughout the long night; even so neither got much sleep, with the howling of the beasts and the gradual disappearance of the droids, one by one until there were none left, just themselves.  They could hear something scratching at the metal work of the pod; it sounded like metal claws and very heavy breathing, as it managed to prise open the door.  Crouched in the corner, Max and Sarden could see the red eyes of the beast approaching them, drool dripping to the floor from its sharp teeth; but then suddenly it stopped, sniffed the air, its features softened and it looked enquiringly at Max and Sarden.  Sarden held out his protein food bar to the beast, who after 5 minutes of hesitation took it out of his hand, licked his outstretched hand, requesting more. Fortunately, they had a large supply of food and they realised that starvation was driving the beasts to attack the compound, and with more supplies being regularly sent, the beasts and the tourists could coexist in harmony.

It was the first day of summer holidays.Jack and Sophie couldn't part away and decided to spend this lovely Monday together.Walking along the seashore they suddenly noticed something  in the bushes.There was an really old boat. It condition indicated that it had been there for a long time. Friends come closer and decided to sail because the overall condition of boat was satisfying. They didn't notice the small hole in the middle of the  deck.This day had a very sad ending .

We departed from Earth 3 years ago.   We reached this planet called Venus.  They thought it wasn't livable, but we proved them wrong!  We settled, we built, we grew, and now two of us are meant to become parents.   We have built our own houses, and food but we're still missing something.  A Sheriff, I ran, almost like a President campaign, and guess what?  I won!   Didn't expect that, but thought I should send you a letter to let you know.

On the planet zoom there lived a ginger haired gnome queen called Lola and ruled over the planet zoom with her trusty sidekick half cat half alien called charlie. Charlie roamed the land searching for invaders and traitors to Lola. Lola would cast spells on anyone or anything that caused harm to her loyal subjects which included differnet species from othe planets who had escaped persecution or the risk of death on there home planet, and they were made to feel welcome and cared for on planet zoom. Lola encouraged the new comers to intigrate into the community and to aslo embrace there own traditons and beliefs. This worked extremely well and the locals loved learning about different planets and traditions they had never seen before. One day charlie caught invaders from another planet trying to take back some of their people who had fled their home planet. Charlie took the to the queen who turned them all in miniature gnomes and made the help all the newcomers on the planet as punishment. Lola continued as queen for years and made sure all her subjects helped each other, and made all her subjects aware of how important being kind and excepting of different cultures and traditions regardless of where you come from.

I was on a plane when it was forced to do an emergency landing in the jungle.  I escaped from the plane and began wondering around the jungle.  I found a treasure map and started following it to find the treasure.  I eat animals for food and rainwater for water.  I encountered dangerous animals, challenging riddles and impossible physical hurdles to get over.  at one time I encountered a tiger that i had to run away and hide from.  I reached an ancient city that no one has come across before.  It was here that I found a pot of gold and i was eventually rescued becoming a very rich man.

Luella struggled to stay upright as the strong gusts of wind blew against her and the boat suddenly swayed beneath her.  When she set out for a new life in America, little did she imagine that it would be a fight for survival to get there.  Tired of having barely enough food to stop her stomach cramping in pain at night, Luella had eagerly grabbed the opportunity to become a governess to the two young children of the local squire.  The children - where were the children now?  Luella realised that she had been so focused on keeping her  balance that she had stopped watching them.  Looking across the misty deck she could see one of her young charges was sheltering beneath a seat but the other?  She saw young Amelia desperately trying to hang on to the railings and not be swept over.  With a sudden burst of energy, Luella rushed forward and grabbed the young girl's dress, pulling her violently away from the edge just before the next strong gust.

After we crash landed in the jungle, we discovered that we were ill-eqipped to survive here. There were trees surrounding us in every direction and we couldn't hear any water nearby. There were five of us with varying degrees of injury; some of us had broken bones, others were just banged up.  We first made sure that we had everything we needed from the small plane, then we set out on our way through the dense jungle. I lead the way with a piece of debris from the plane, using it to slash through when needed, closely following me was my friend Mark and our families. We had no other supplies with us so we were looking out for anything we could eat and some water to drink, then suddenly we heard it. A shrill scream in the distance. We went charging towards it not even thinking to stop.

I was on holiday in Thailand and had gone for a walk near the jungle but had got lost so I looked around me hoping to see someone who could help.  But there was nobody there so I tried to make my way back through the jungle to the hotel as best I could.   I entered the jungle with trepidation, it was dark and overgrown with many strange noises but I carried on. Suddenly I came to a clearing and an old woman was sitting by a small fire and she called me over and said she could get me back if I was happy to ride her elephant who knew the way.  A large animated elephant appeared and spoke to me saying he would get me back safely but I would need to hang on tight.  I climbed into the golden saddle he had on his back and prepared for a bumpy ride back but suddenly he roared and started pawing at the ground.  Within seconds he unfolded wings from his back and we took off up to the sky through the jungle canopy, flying fast and free through the sky, over the trees and away.  With a massive bump we landed back at the hotel but I was in my bed and there was no sign of the elephant - it had all been a very strange dream.

Tim was about to start his degree in archaeology once the summer was over, but before that, he was on the adventure of a lifetime, on safari with his father. It was his last day and they had gone deeper into the jungle than they had ever been before. All of a sudden the weather had taken a turn for the worse and Tim had become separated from the main group. Stumbling around in the torrential rainfall, he slipped and stumbled down a deep ravine. He rolled and bounced through the vegetation for what felt like an eternity finally coming to rest at the bottom. He cleared his head and looked around in confusion. The rain had stopped, the sun was shining and there was no sign of the monsoon that had been raging before his fall.  As he looked around he was shocked to see what looked like an entire city rising tall above the trees in the distance.

What a month, it's a miracle that we are alive but thanks to Captain Tom; alive we are, where in the first week we were hit by the worst storms I have ever had the misfortune of seeing, but the savviness of our good Captain and his sailing abilities kept us afloat. We were then boarded by pirates, and all seemed lost until Tom struck a deal with them to keep us alive and handed over "treasure" of which had no value. He also enacted a clever ploy where we snuck a crewmate off ship and sank their ship in the meantime, truly a remarkable feat. Before we could even celebrate our victory over the scourge, fog and mist, and the dreaded Kraken descended upon us and caused absolute terror. 4 Crew members were sadly lost, but yet again through the leadership and refusal to die from our captain again we prevailed. We were stranded and lost, running out of food and water, the thought of mutiny and survival weighed heavily on my mind but not our captain's, whose optimism and determination shone like a light and kept us going. Against all the odds, he had done it, an unimaginable amount of the finest treasures were ours to have and our status in history was truly immortalised against all the odds. It saddens me that I will not be there to see it, greed took hold of me and I stole more than I share, alas I must now walk the plank.

Three friends, Alex, Maya, and Ben, were transported to the planet Zorgog. They encountered a colour changing river and talking rocks. The planet faced a catastrophe caused by an angry star. Determined to save the indigenous species, they embarked on a mission. Guided by the rocks, they found an artefact to calm the star. With their united strength, they succeeded and restored harmony. Returning to Earth, they carried precious memories and inspiring tales of their adventure. The power of friendship prevailed on the mysterious planet Zorgog.

There lived a man called George.  George was born and lost in the jungle where he was brought up by monkeys.  George lived an adventurous life playing and jumping with monkeys.  when he reached the age of 18, he stumbled accross a lady called Fiona whose father and his men came to the jungle to capture animals.  George fell in love with fiona.  Fiona's father was against the love between his daughter and george.  At the end, George got married to fiona after much struggle.  Fiona,s father finally blessed their union.

Three astronauts who were very curious learn more mysteries came together to go on a mission. They embarked on a perilous mission to explore the mysteries of Zogar. Zogar is a remote planet known for its rare elements and resplendent beauty. During this mission they encountered strange elements, bizarre creatures and unexpected challenges, testing wits and courage. Through teamwork and determination, they overcame all the obstacles they encountered on their way. Their exploration was able to give humanity invaluable insights into a totally alien world. today other scientist now travel to those planets with knowledge and possible expectations. More and more astronauts are now emerging to go and explore other mysteries in different planets.

In a whole different world, Benji, Robin and Maya crash land into the planet Spherus. As experimental scientists, they have been tasked with finding alien lifeforms to better further the understanding of the human race. Upon arrival, Maya whispers "Stop! Look after there", Robin and Benji stunned and slowly turn their heads. They are in awe as they spot a civilization of creatures, that look very similar to them. They appear to be much more advanced, capable of helping the human race in their task of saving their dying resources. They engage in conversations with the creatures, luckily the life forms have technology which can translate any language, they are friendly and agree to further negotiations. Name the greenus species, they set out plans to help the human race survive, But all of this comes at a cost right?

On a planet far away, two space explorers land their craft. They came looking for rare minerals. As they made their way through a dense sand storm, they discovered a lush forest. They discovered strange but friendly creatures. They made their way through the trees and found a temple which had instructions on where to find the minerals that they were searching for. They followed the map and found the minerals. With their mission complete they returned to their craft. They returned to their home planet as heros.

The boy raced off to sea for the adventure of his life, not that he knew it yet. What was meant to be a trip to clear plastic waste suddenly an all out adventure when he fell overboard unnoticed by the rest of the crew. Up to this point everything had gone to plan and they were returning to harbour with a boat full of plastic waste. As he was looking out at the ocean still littered with waste a rouge wave came out of no where any threw him overboard. Hitting the freezing cold sea with a panic he caught he breath and looked for assistance from the ship. Instead of the expected life ring on a rope, nothing. The boat disappeared into the distance as the crew hadn't seen what had happen. Now the plastic he had come to remove from the ocean would be his only chase of survival.

The generation starship went into orbit around Theta, the first new planet to be visited by humans.It had been travelling from Earth for 2000 years and now Jake was ready to travel to the surface in the lander craft.After landing he got out with his crew of eight others and looked around at the surface structures which looked exotic,just like pictures of rain forests once found on Earth.The trees nearby swayed and shifted in the light breeze and Jake saw the first alien life form ever seen .The creature had a round head but with lots of small eyes which covered the top half and the rest of the body looked more like a beetle.It crept toward the crew who looked at Jake asking with their gazes what they should do.He stepped forward slowly and approached the alien who held out its arm like structure to him.He held out his own arm in greeting and touched the alien but suddenly the rest of the crew saw them both disappear from view and did not know what to do next.

Abigail was on an expedition in the jungle to aid her research into ancient civilisations.  While trekking through the jungle she became separated from the rest of her team and found herself completely lost.  She had to face dangerous animals, treacherous terrain and inhospitable weather.   She stumbled across a river which she decided to follow downstream.  She discovered inner strength, courage and bravery she never knew she has as she spent days travelling along the river bank.  She survived on her meagre rations and some fruits she found in the jungle.  After 7 days lost in the jungle she finally came across a small village where she found food, water and shelter thanks to the local people.  The locals in the village were able to give her invaluable information about the ancient civilisations that used to dominate the jungle.

A group of five daring friends find an ancient treasure map and decide to explore the vast jungles of the Amazon to retrieve the legendary golden monkey statue. Encountering deadly snakes, secret booby traps, and feuding tribes along their journey, their brotherhood is tested. In the end, they survive the perils of the jungle, discovering not only the treasured artifact but also a newfound respect for nature and their friendship.   However, not all goes well during their explanation. At times the friends face serious challenges that risk their lives. However, they also find the time in the jungle strengthens their friendship and helps them appreciate things that they did not know about themselves. All of the friends who entered the jungle came out as different, better people. Now the explorers are planning other, safer journeys where they can continue their adventures.

Once upon a time there was an adventurer called Hercule that decided to undertake a jungle expedition. He started began to plan the route, journey and then purchased his plane tickets. Once landed he organised a guide and all the required equipment. The journey started well, but soon he ran into a forgotten tribe that didn't take kindly to strangers. They captured him and decided they wanted to sacrifice him to appease their god, but he managed to escape. The remainder of the jungle expedition went well with very little issues. Hercule completed it in record time and was heralded for this feat. He returned home to a heroes welcome and a family that were very happy to see him!

Ice was added to a cup.   Then lemonade was added to the cup.  The cup was carried into another room.  Then the cup was then placed on a coaster on a table.  Then the cup was picked up but slipped and feel to the floor.   The cup shattered and broke into many pieces.  The lemonade and ice was spilt all over the floor.  A nearby cloth was used to wipe up the mess caused by the cup being spilt.

John is a fifteen year old living in Rwanda with his parents. One day John decided to go into the jungle near his home. There he came across a family of orang-utans, who didn't seem to mind his presence, in fact they seemed to be welcoming him. Two of the younger orang-utans came over to John and peered at him curiously. The one of the older ones came over and dragged the youngsters away, and seemed to be glowering at John, which made him very nervous. He decided he should return home soon, as he was getting rather scared. But before he could he was grabbed from behind by another orang-utan. Then they all fell on him and started beating him and biting him.

He wiped the sweat from his brow and steadied himself against the trunk of a squat tree as he gathered his breath. He knew that he must have finally got away from them as all had been silent behind him for what seemed like an hour now. He grabbed at his drinking canteen at his belt and unscrewed the lid, greedily tipping the last few precious drops of its contents into his mouth. This was a problem, he needed to find water and he needed to find it fast. Ok, think, rationalise, work out where I am the man thought to himself. It was not long past sunrise and it was very dark, the part of the hungle he was in was extremely dense and the trees and flora blotted out most of the sky. He had started off running southwards following he river but quickly realised that was a bad idea. He had taken a left, East, into the trees.

Kimbo and Jessie's honeymoon was not supposed to end in an Amazon jungle. They were in a wonderful hotel and went on a sightseeing tour that made them end up in the jungle. They were scammed and left to die after having been robbed by the sightseeing team. The canopy of forgery provided little reprieve from the lurking dangers. They were blessed to find fruit but knew that the supply would not last. A lion,  sneaked up behind them and showed them his big mouth. Kimbo and Jessie screamed and ran for their lives. Until they heard gunshots.

After losing their fishing boat in a merciless storm, John Anderson and his dog, Buster, embark on an unexpected journey surviving on a life raft in the middle of the Pacific Ocean. They encounter ruthless pirates, large marine animals and endure harsh weather conditions. In their quest to survive, they discover an uncharted island guarded only by an old wickery gate. John battles the crashing waves and beaches his raft, he leaps off with Buster and explores the small abandoned island when he suddenly sees a glowing chest. His eyes bulge with excitement and he runs over until suddenly a group of pirates appear out of nowhere and start attacking John. John with the help of Buster and his old pistol defeat the pirates without even suffering a scratch! He walks over to the glowing chest and opens it, it flips back and the piercing light of treasure lights up the island. John and Buster have done it, he attaches rope to the chest and pulls it back to his raft.

As human civilisation progresses to 2356. Advances are made in intergalactic spacecraft technology. A new planet is found for a lucky 6 rich businessmen. Planet x1 is green and vast with pools and jungles. Everything on the planet is edible. Its a magical world with time portals and teleportation black holes to each area of the planet. The exploration is at first treated as a holiday and the businessmen enjoy there time exploring many wonders. But soon unbeknown to all the research disaster strikes! Out of caves walk aliens with with weapons to freeze enemy's and terrorise

There was a young man who has recently turned from boy to man, he is called Steven,he went to bed and fell asleep after a long day working, he woke up to a strange sensation, strange smell and strange sites, he has realised he is no longer in his bedroom but in what can only be described as a different planet!     A few months later, the young man is now exploring the planet with what can only be described as a unknown creature, with some human like aspects, they are exploring every crevice, room and building on this planet, looking for any other sign of life.      As the young man and known creature walked around this unusual planet, they heard a rattle of a crate and then BANG, it burst into pieces and the creature had zoomed off, it was slimy, green and only arms length in size.     Steven and the unknown friend chased and chased after the green unknown entity, until it lost the pair of them and out of sight.     Curious as to what it was, Steven and his friend carried on exploring the planet. They both realised they had travelled too far as now there seemed to be less life and buildings around them. As they turned around to head back in the direction they had been they noticed the change in temperature and a eerie feeling overcome them. As they carried on travelling, they heard unbearable screaming noise, in the far distance, Steven's friend noticed the green slimy creature approaching but this time with an army of them, the creature teleported off, leaving Steven stranded on his own!

Five teenagers embarked on an adventure, with alot of excitements. They wanted to reveal the ancient secrets and in search of a treasures in the dense jungle. They followed their maps, till they got to a hidden cave in the middle of the jungle, Two of them were curious and wanted to know what was inside,  The two got their lamps out and decided to go inside, and the rest decided to continue with the walk in the jungle . After an hour the two boys came carrying a treasure that was hidden inside for years and no one else managed to find it. The other three went to the far end of the forest where they found a stream of magic water that when you touch it you could see your future. they took out all their bottles and filled them with the water. They went back and joined the rest. They emerged from the jungle , and they were recorded in the world book of record for their braveness and saving a life.

He didn't know where Guam was. It wasn't a place he'd ever heard of in school, but for some reason the army had decided it would be ideal for an Ohio farm boy to spend two years of the war hacking out the jungle to build a field hospital to prepare for the invasion of Japan. At least he knew where Japan was; he was pretty sure on that. The heat was unnatural, he'd decided. Couldn't be natural. Humans can't live here. Couldn't they carve through the forest at night, when it was cooler? Is this an experiment, is the whole of the Pacific all as unbearable as this place he couldn't find on a map if the Lord willed him?

Max woke with a start, his alarm was blaring, he knew this would happen, he's going to be late. The crew of the X9CHAP had touched down on the surface of planet AlphaD3J just two days ago, and he was struggling to get his body clock accustomed to the new day lengths here. Everyone else had adjusted nearly immediately, but he still just couldn't get up in time, and now he was going to pay the price.    The leader of the expedition to AlphaD3J, a scientist by the name of Dr Green, was very clear about this. If he was late one more time he'd be in trouble. Rushing to get himself ready, Max threw on his exploration suit, tripping over his grav-boots as he went, and rushed towards the hatch that would take him outside.     He entered the door code and the large metal door gently opened itself and revealed the lush environment of his new home. Stretching out before him were fields of purple grass, with hab units like the one he'd just left dotted about the place in the typical community structure, it was time to go.

As we approached the ship that was holding Beartrice prisoner, they began to prepare for battle.    '' We must get alongside them as quickly as possible'' said captain Hamish.    I drew my sword and prepared to board the vessel, a fear filled my shaking body.    Within seconds there was a roar and a large commotion as we flew through the air between ships, fighting for our lives as we landed on the bloodied deck.    We managed to take control, and went below to find Beatrice.    However, it was a trap and Beatrice had betrayed us.    She had taken up with the rouge of the wandering sea and had led us to him.    We had no choice but to surrender, but this was not the end.

Scientists and politicians argued for months over what this new planet should be called, those countries seeking to be the first to land there had competing suggestions.    The Chinese would name it after their long term leader, the Americans were undecided but most suggestions centred around a concept of freedom and exploration, Earth Apollo was the most popular for now.     Several years ago each mission began to get there, to reach this new uninhabited Earth. A tiny Earth that floated unseen for centuries on the other side of the Solar System, within reach of man and its newest technology.     It started with a Russian failure, a Japanese catastrophe and set backs in Europe. As we were accustomed to however the Americans prevailed to an extent.     Contact was lost days ago, the landing was unsuccessful but over a dozen of its first inhabitants lived for the first week; then the naming of the planet would come down to one man, the sole survivor who had no means yet of telling anyone he had made it. Anyone who arrived next would come to understand it would be called Planet Dale.

This morning I woke up and drew back the curtains. The sun had already risen and it was a lovely bright day outside. I ran down to the harbour and jumped into my boat and sailed out to sea. Before I had gone very far I saw a group of dolphins leaping out of sea and set my course to follow them. They went close to the sea cliffs where there plenty of fish to eat. I got out my fishing rod to see if I could catch anything and after a while I felt a tug on my fishing line. I pulled and pulled and eventually I was able to pull a fish into the boat. It was a lovely mackerel, just the right size for my tea so I headed back to the harbour, mission accomplished!

On a sun-kissed morning, aboard the majestic vessel named Ocean's Fury, a group of intrepid friends embarked on a daring adventure across the open seas. Guided by an ancient map rumoured to lead to a hidden treasure, they navigated through treacherous waves and whispered legends. With salty air filling their lungs and determination igniting their spirits, they braved storms that threatened to engulf them. Along the way, they encountered enigmatic mermaids who sang haunting melodies and wise old sea turtles that shared tales of forgotten civilizations. As the sun dipped below the horizon, casting its golden hues upon the endless expanse, they finally reached the fabled island. Digging beneath the moonlit sky, they unearthed chests overflowing with jewels, artifacts, and secrets lost to time. With hearts ablaze and dreams realized, they sailed home, forever marked by the profound beauty and untamed spirit of the open seas. This story was forever told to children to help them get to sleep.

When a group of friends, passionate about wildlife photography, venture into the untouched Amazonian rainforest, they unexpectedly come across a forgotten indigenous tribe. They help the tribe combat a dangerous disease with their knowledge of modern medicine. Their adventurous journey not only yields breathtaking pictures but also creates a lasting bond with an ancient culture. A young biologist, Lisa, Leads an expedition into an untouched Amazon jungle in search of a mythical healing plant. Battling deadly wildlife, treacherous terrains, and a rival treasure-hunting group, her team's resilience and unity are put to the ultimate test. After unexpected betrayals and loss, Lisa finds not only the covered plant but also a newfound respect for the mystic wilderness and the power of perseverance. A young brave explorer named Jake embarks on a daring journey to retrieve an ancient artifact rumored to be hidden deep within the amazon jungle. Along the way, he encounters dangerous wildlife, treacherous terrains, and tests of character, yet remains undeterred by the challenging conditions.

The girl pushed the small boat into the softly lapping waves. The sun shone onto her head and back as she felt the sand disappear between her toes. Gracefully she pulled herself into the small vessel as it bobbed up and down over the gently turquoise -green waves. Her heart soared; she was free! She felt the wind tug at her hair and catch the sails as they arched into the sea breezes. From the boat she could see the wild grass clinging to the cliff tops. The white feathered birds circled overhead. She felt alive!

We landed, finally, all safe and sound everything still intact, it was a worrying time but we made it. We cannot believe the vivid colours on this planet it is like nothing we have ever seen before, it is beautiful, breath taking i wish there were other who could see it, so we unload get our backpacks and start walking, we have no idea which direction to go as everything just looks so nice, as we start to walk this little blue animal appears, what is it, will it hurt us, it hides behind the rainbow coloured tree peeping at us, we are all a bit scared if i am honest. we don't know what it is going to do, we stand still as bot to scare it, it cones out and it smiles, this big huge goofy warm smile and comes out and walks towards us, it then turns and hand gestures for us to follow, should we? is it safe? is it a trap? there is only one way to find out, lets go! it leads us deep into this bright forest with strange fruits hanging from the trees, then we see even more of these funny creatures, all different colours! it is truly magical, they all stand looking at us, then after a few minutes they all come towards us carrying food and drinks!

A team of adventures travelled to the Pacific Ocean to try find a monster that has been stalking certain area of the sea. They have found the monster and tried to kill it however during the harsh waves of the sea they did not. The monster instead attacked the boat and the mother nature of the storms damaged the boat badly. The crew got out of the boat and the monster dragged them into the deep sea. The monster then bit into each member of the team and slowly turning the adventures into monsters. The army got called out to help these adventures but it was too late. The army was also attacked by the monsters and dragged down the sea. The same fate awaits for anyone else who would dare to come after the vile monster.

When Toby got off the school bus that morning he had no idea that his day was going to end up taking him to the middle of the jungle.   yet here he was face to face with both a monkey and a parrot. neither seemed particularly interested in him they where far to focused on his backpack for that.   Toby took the bag off his shoulders and opened it in front of his new friends. before he got the chance to look inside though the monkey snatched the bag and ran as the parrott screached what sounded like a laugh and flew after his friend. Toby gave chase through the forest as fast as he could but the monkey was faster. eventually tired and out of breath Toby sat on a fallen tree defeated and alone.   Toby took a slow look round as he realized he had no idea where he was.

The seas were angry and rugged, throwing itself and making a point of letting it be known, like a monster from another world ready to swallow anything up. All the passengers huddled under the cover of the tables , whilst the ferry tried to negotiate waves, which were in no mood for negotiating with a mere piece of metal. The vessel was thrown around as easy as throwing a small stone with little or no effort and the thrashing water continuously slapped it from every angle, like a boxer going for a knockdown.    And then silence. As if it had never happened. The sea was calm once more and the skies were blue and cheery. It all seemed like a dream. The passengers didn't move.

It had been three days since Paul had seen any sign of other human life. The cargo ship that had passed him by had been totally oblivious to the small dinghy being flooded by the trail of its wake and the young man clinging desperately to its sides. There was plenty of life around Paul however: dolphins often joined him, swimming alongside the tiny craft and leaping high into the air, as if to cheer him up and take his mind of his terrible predicament. It didn't. He wondered often how a short trip to the seaside and his desire to have a shot in his friend's dinghy had resulted in this. He knew people would be looking for him and couldn't understand why he hadn't been spotted yet but the squall that had arisen suddenly had been ferocious and he'd felt powerless to do anything himself. He knew he was lucky to have survived at all. He didn't want to think about how much longer that would be true.

Three friends, Julie, David and Lucy were on a long walk through the very hot jungle, hearing strange sounds, ticking, whooping and every now and again some screaming. David said - is this a good idea to come somewere we have never been to before? Lucy though was well up for adventures like this and usually when Lucy went for something Julie would follow her lead as fun was the result of such days she spent with Lucy. Lucy looked at David with high eyebrows and a ruefull smile and since David was very keen on being more than just a friend with Lucy he walked faster into to darker jungle to show he was not afraid.    A large spider up on a massive dark green leaf made Julie gasp but she moved on like the other two. They stopped for a while to look at a beautiful red and purple flower with at least five buzzing bees hovering in and out of it's centre. But with a whoosing sound they turned quickly to see a spear hitting high up on the overgrowth and three seconds later the spear fell to the ground with a blue and yellow bird attached to it. Two men almost naked rushed in from the undergrowth shouting and whooping with what the three friends could not tell was pleasure or something else far more worrisome for the young explorers.

It began on a cold, dark night. The seas were roaring and the crew were determined. It was the adventure of a lifetime, no one wanted to return home empty-handed and everyone was determined to do whatever it took to return as heroes. The treasure they sought was a long distance away, it was a perilous journey but the spoils would be worth the effort. Every man was working together to ensure sure and steady progress towards the final destination, they wouldn't let tiredness or pain deter them. The captain was considerate of the efforts made and was just as much involved as every other crew mate. Everyone knew how important the treasure was, it would mean huge growth for the town when they returned. No man, creature or element would stop them.

I set out in my little rowing boat for an adventure on the seas.  It was very cold so i wore a big coat and a hat.  I also wore gloves to keep my hands warm.  The sea was very choppy making my progress very slow.  Despite rowing against the current i slowly moved forward.  I rowed and rowed until i could see an island ahead.  As i got closer to the island i dropped down a weight on a rope to hold the boat in one place.  I then took out a rod and began to fish.

when a young astronomer, Leo discovers a new planet he embarks on a thrilling adventure into the unknown. The planet is unlike anything he's seen before, brightly coloured plants in pinks, purples and blues, tall rock like formations petruding from the ground and o soft almost cushion feeling below his feet. He is scared and excited at the same time, he cannot see any signs of life but is aware there could be, he moves slowly through the overgrown foliage, he takes in the smell, one like hes never smelt before, strange but pleasant, the soft wiring sound in the air and the total stillness of his surroundings. He notices openings in some of the rocks, possible doors he thought. the thought of finding life was both extremely exciting and terrifying, he tentatively moves towards the openings. he notices a pond nearby, well what we would describe as a pond here, however it didnt look like water, it had a more slimy consistancy. he reached an opening on one of the rocks and called inside, no response, tentatively he steps inside..

One day, three friends decided to go a journey out to see in a boat owned by own of their families. They lived near lots of islands and secluded bays that they had never explored before. However, they did not look at a weather forecast beforehand and as they neared a particularly remote island they were battered by a storm. There was nowhere to drop anchor and they did not thing they were survive. And then, they spotted a huge sea creature, unknown to science circling their boat. They were really scared and the sea creature knocked over their boat and they fell into the sea. The following morning they awoke washed up on the beach of the island, barely alive. One of the friends then spotted a treasure chest jutting out from the sand further down the beach.

Three young astronauts went on an adventurous journey to planet Kazzi. On their way, they were thrilled and hoped to experience non harmful but splendid visit.  On hitting the planet, their ship slowed down and became out of control. They hit a rock and the ship stopped. Getting down from the ship, they noticed the habitant to be built like animation and no one talked to them but they were staring at the ship while passing by.   Zoe saw a middle aged girl and approached her and to her surprise, they speak English. The girl was friendly enough and decided to show them around. This was getting exciting as they began exploring Planet Kazzi.

Solo rower Jake Kent is heading out on a mission to cross the Atlantic in a row boat. He plans to do this with the support of a back up team.  The back up team will have supplies of food and water, but they cannot assist Jake in the physical aspects of his journey.  Jake has been in training for over 18 months and plans to set off in the next few days.  He has to wait for the weather condition to be right, but if he doesn't set off soon he will miss the best forecast weather for his trip.  Eventually the stars align and the weather breaks, Jake will set off the next day.  He is anxious and excited for what lies ahead.  Is he up to this.

I lay there as my head pressed against the grass and the jungle trees tickled against my arm.   'Hello,' I heard behind me. I turned around to see who it was but couldn't see anyone.   'Helloo, excuse me... down here.' I felt a pinch on my foot and saw a little goblin standing by my foot.

As tom idly sits on his games console playing the the latest football game, his mind began to wander, he thought 'i need to do something, anything, an adventure!' he thought. He happened to know of his dads sailing boat next to the harbour and off he went, packed a bag and sailed off into the sea. He steered the boat awaiting what adventures would bestow him as he sailed, with the waves crashing against the sail and he thought to himself 'maybe this was not a wise idea today'. Further ahead he saw what looked like a island, this is strange he thought as he looked at this mysterious land which looked isolated, but his intrigue over fear made his sail further on and he sailed on towards it and the island had a dark gloomy atmosphere and he thought to himself maybe i should not explore this further! Then suddenly a big bang, and crash and to his absolute shock what looked like a shark hammered into the side of the boat making the boat rock to its core and the adrenaline began build in tome and suddenly before he knew it he was thrown onto the island! After feeling shaken from the fall he got up and looked around and saw the dark surroundings of the island and thought this is not the adventure i needed today, and thankfully the boat capsized onto the sand and the shark swam off looking for its next prey and tom went on and sat on the sand thinking what to do next! He saw something shiny in the sand, a small wooden box and his curiosity and instinct told him to take it and whether it was a good idea or not he gathered himself went on the boat and sailed off back home, hoping it was a safer journey back than getting here and he thought to himself 'maybe i should just play on the console in future!

Five school boys are about to have the best time of their lives.They have all agreed to go on an adventure in the jungle. They are accompanied by a group of teachers. The five school boys are looking for animals not familiar to the. They come across lots of snakes and spiders. Also there are monkeys swinging from trees. Their are rangers that patrol the outer bits of the jungle to keep everyone safe.The boys jump in the rangers van to explore deeper in the jungle ,but in a safe space.

The captain stared out from his position on the bridge. The sea was slate grey and looked angry, he thought. The wind was whipping up and the captain pulled his collar up to shelter from the biting cold. He had been on plenty missions like this before, but this was a different proposition altogether. At first, he had thought the President must have been mistaken, and that this was a wild goose chase. But as he peered through his binoculars, he realised that the intelligence had been correct. After a thousand years and countless more stories and theories, he was looking straight at it. Atlantis.

A crew of daring explorers set foot on a fascinating planet in the far reaches of the galaxy. Their senses were fascinated by the planet's lush forest and bright flora, as strange species roamed freely, releasing melodious  chirps and phosphorescent colours. The explorers followed an ancient map in search of a fabled artefact said to have remarkable powers. They saw ethereal beings known as the Luminae, who shimmered within an otherworldly radiance as they advanced deeper into the planet unexplored landscape. The Luminae offered guidance and safety revealing the artifacts location at the core of long forgotten temple. the explorers entered the hallowed room, where the artefacts pulsed with energy, after overcoming difficult challenges and completing intricate puzzles. They clutched the artefacts with shaky hands, a surge of strength through their veins. However, as they made their triumphal escape, the planet began to tremble, its ecosystem awoken by the extraction of the artefacts. They almost fled the planets grasps, leaving behind a world forever changed by their brave quest

Sarah did not sign up for such an arduous mission when she joined Starfleet, but after the warp drive disintegrated and the auto pilot crashed her into Zorax, she had little choice but to succeed. Whilst she had seen many different star systems and planets wholly unlike the last, the beauty and drama of Zorax was like nothing she had seen previously. From the gas clouds, crystalline rain, down to the plants and even the soil, it was like Sarah was a newborn exploring how the world worked with no frame of reference. Luckily, the creatures that inhabited the planet were not either incredibly hostile nor completely afraid as was the norm on planetary excursions, and she was able to live a peaceful coexistence with them. Over some time, this coexistence became a friendship, and an understanding of their communication through much trial and error meant that Sarah was able to become a part of their society. This society then revealed their most pressing need; the recovery of their ancient orb which had been lost in tribal warfare many centuries ago, that was crucial for the true succession of a ruler to unify their people. Sarah agreed to find this orb using the technological advances granted to her by the remainder of her original flight suit, and what was salvageable from the craft that was now slowly becoming part of the jungle. After much searching, the orb was located in the bowels of a deep chasm in the jungle, where a breakaway tribe guarded it with a simple demand: if Sarah was willing to take her life, the orb would be returned to its original resting place.

The jungle beckoned. They had decided on this long, long ago, when they first met at the sweet age of 5. "When I grow up, I'm gonna explore the jungle." Andrew exclaimed, "I'm coming!" his friend James chimed in. "Me too!" said Monica. Little did they know that this innocent plan for adventure would lead to the death of one of them, not twenty years later.

Two best friends decide to go on a jungle adventure to Africa.  On arrival on their first night they pitch up their tents and settle down for the night.  They are awoken suddenly by voices close by.  They lay silent listening.  The voices are getting closer.  They hold their breath as shadows appear outside.  What should they do?  Quietly, they slowly begin to unzip the tent door.

A daring group of explorers set out on a journey across the uncharted open seas looking for long lost treasure.    The ship is cold and wet, they have been on the sea for months now with nothing to show, when suddenly the whole ship is shaken by a giant boom thunder strikes and the whole ship is awaken, tired and exhausted sailors come to life as if possessed, They look up and see an enormous ship sporting black flags when suddenly the ship is hit by cannon fire, wood, dust and splinters are thrown in every directions as the rain brings it all back down.    The door of the captain's quarters swing open as we see a skinny young man step out, he tries to yells out order after order but one can barely hear over the cannon fire and screaming the crew rush to the stations with a sparkle in their eye, this is what they have been waiting for.    Cannons shoot through the air back and forth going through both ships like paper, the pirate ship with the black sails did not account for this ship to have so much fight in them the captain shouts with all his might "Aim for the back" so loud even the pirate ship could have heard him. Cannons hit the back where the gunpowder is stored and a big light comes from the ship then an explosion so big it throws back the crew to the ground.  The pirate ship is up in flames, half torn from the explosion and part sinking.     They have survived but barely, the ship is illuminated by a light from clouds splitting, the whole ship freeze, as they look to the sea they notice that the split in the cloud has created a line of sunshine leading them right to a small island, Thunder in every direction except for the sunny island sprawling with colours.   "This is it", the captain whispers, as they weather starts to calm down.

A group of adventurous teenagers ventures into a jungle. Mia discovers a mysterious artifact. As a result, unseen forces haunt the group, driven by a vengeful spirit. Mia delves deeper into the forest and the mystery. The spirit finally reveals itself, fueled by rage. Mia unravels the artifact's secret and binds the spirit. The jungle is restored to peaceful serenity. The group returns home, forever changed by their supernatural encounter.

She sat back in the padded chair, terrified; the countdown to launch was about to begin. Ten to-one came and went and she couldn't believe the feeling of weightlessness as the rocket sped to her new home: Gilga-3. Once arriving, she was welcomed by those who had flown there before her and was shown to her dormitory. The first day was exciting and surreal and she was shown around by a teenage boy who pointed out all the wildlife and points of interest they had currently found.    "Here is a Lonsha: It's like a rabbit but much smaller; and here is a Mount: It's like a gerbil but much larger."    The boy helped her around most of the day before giving her her daily duties for the following weeks. With her sharpshooting skills, she was to help the boy's dad hunt for food and explore some of the areas the citizens hadn't yet searched. The girl felt involved and well looked after here and at a first glance decided that this trip was the best thing she had ever done.

Susie and her friends climbed aboard the ship. It had washed ashore the previous day, and they had been debating since then whether to start this adventure or not. As soon as they entered the ship they knew they had made the right decision, a key in the ignition meant that they were able to begin their journey without thinking any further. Jack, Susie's best friend, turned the key and the ship began to start up. He turned the wheel away from the shore and they began to sail out to sea. They sailed for around 40 minutes on smooth waters before things started to go wrong! Soon the waters began to get choppy, and the further they went the choppier they were. Susie began to regret pushing this idea of an adventure o the open seas immediately.

It was the first time anyone had ever stood foot on Mars.  The Astronaughts emerged from the tiny landing capsule one by one, cautious but excited to see their new world.  It was nice to be outside, after being couped up inside a tin can for all those months, almost overwhelming.  The red desert, pock-marked with craters, sprawled out towards the horizon, a barren wasteland as far as the eye could see.  This was no time for sightseeing though, the team had work to do.  First job was to anchor the Lander, and start errecting the shelter, which looked like little more than a silver awning which attached to the side of the capsule.  Crate after crate were unclipped from the Landing module, oxygen, supplies, scientific equipment, even bedding and folding furniture.  This was going to be their home for the forseeable future, what adventures will Mars have in store for them?
